var book = {
	"name": "2 Kings",
	"numChapters": 25,
	"chapters": {
		"1": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">1 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9535A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9535A\"></sup>After the death of Ahab, Moab <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9535B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9535B\"></sup>rebelled against Israel.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Now Ahaziah fell through the lattice in his upper chamber in Samaria, and lay sick; so he sent messengers, telling them, “Go, inquire of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9536C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9536C\"></sup>Baal-zebub, the god of Ekron, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9536D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9536D\"></sup>whether I shall recover from this sickness.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>But the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Elijah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9537E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9537E\"></sup>the Tishbite, “Arise, go up to meet the messengers of the king of Samaria, and say to them, ‘Is it because there is no God in Israel that you are going to inquire of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9537F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9537F\"></sup>Baal-zebub, the god of Ekron?",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Now therefore thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9538G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9538G\"></sup>You shall not come down from the bed to which you have gone up, but you shall surely die.’” So Elijah went.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The messengers returned to the king, and he said to them, “Why have you returned?”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And they said to him, “There came a man to meet us, and said to us, ‘Go back to the king who sent you, and say to him, Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, Is it because there is no God in Israel that you are sending to inquire of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9540H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9540H\"></sup>Baal-zebub, the god of Ekron? Therefore you shall not come down from the bed to which you have gone up, but you shall surely die.’”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>He said to them, “What kind of man was he who came to meet you and told you these things?”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>They answered him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9542I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9542I\"></sup>“He wore a garment of hair, with a belt of leather about his waist.” And he said, “It is Elijah the Tishbite.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then the king sent to him a captain of fifty men with his fifty. He went up to Elijah, who was sitting on the top of a hill, and said to him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9543J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9543J\"></sup>“O man of God, the king says, ‘Come down.’”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>But Elijah answered the captain of fifty, “If I am a man of God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9544K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9544K\"></sup>let fire come down from heaven and consume you and your fifty.” Then fire came down from heaven and consumed him and his fifty.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Again the king sent to him another captain of fifty men with his fifty. And he answered and said to him, “O man of God, this is the king's order, ‘Come down quickly!’”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>But Elijah answered them, “If I am a man of God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9546L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9546L\"></sup>let fire come down from heaven and consume you and your fifty.” Then the fire of God came down from heaven and consumed him and his fifty.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Again the king sent the captain of a third fifty with his fifty. And the third captain of fifty went up and came and fell on his knees before Elijah and entreated him, “O man of God, please let my life, and the life of these fifty servants of yours, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9547M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9547M\"></sup>be precious in your sight.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Behold, fire came down from heaven and consumed the two former captains of fifty men with their fifties, but now let my life be precious in your sight.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Elijah, “Go down with him; do not be afraid of him.” So he arose and went down with him to the king",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>and said to him, “Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, ‘Because you have sent messengers to inquire of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9550N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9550N\"></sup>Baal-zebub, the god of Ekron—is it because there is no God in Israel to inquire of his word?—therefore you shall not come down from the bed to which you have gone up, but you shall surely die.’”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>So he died according to the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> that Elijah had spoken. Jehoram became king in his place <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9551O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9551O\"></sup>in the second year of Jehoram the son of Jehoshaphat, king of Judah, because Ahaziah had no son.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Now the rest of the acts of Ahaziah that he did, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel?"
		},
		"2": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">2 </span>Now when the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was about to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9553A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9553A\"></sup>take Elijah up to heaven by a whirlwind, Elijah and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9553B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9553B\"></sup>Elisha were on their way from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9553C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9553C\"></sup>Gilgal.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And Elijah said to Elisha, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9554D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9554D\"></sup>“Please stay here, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has sent me as far as Bethel.” But Elisha said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9554E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9554E\"></sup>“As the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives, and as you yourself live, I will not leave you.” So they went down to Bethel.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9555F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9555F\"></sup>the sons of the prophets who were in Bethel came out to Elisha and said to him, “Do you know that today the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will take away your master from over you?” And he said, “Yes, I know it; keep quiet.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Elijah said to him, “Elisha, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9556G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9556G\"></sup>please stay here, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has sent me to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9556H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9556H\"></sup>Jericho.” But he said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9556I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9556I\"></sup>“As the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives, and as you yourself live, I will not leave you.” So they came to Jericho.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9557J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9557J\"></sup>The sons of the prophets who were at Jericho drew near to Elisha and said to him, “Do you know that today the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will take away your master from over you?” And he answered, “Yes, I know it; keep quiet.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then Elijah said to him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9558K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9558K\"></sup>“Please stay here, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has sent me to the Jordan.” But he said, “As the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives, and as you yourself live, I will not leave you.” So the two of them went on.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Fifty men of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9559L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9559L\"></sup>the sons of the prophets also went and stood at some distance from them, as they both were standing by the Jordan.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then Elijah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9560M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9560M\"></sup>took his cloak and rolled it up and struck the water, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9560N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9560N\"></sup>and the water was parted to the one side and to the other, till the two of them could go over on dry ground.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>When they had crossed, Elijah said to Elisha, “Ask what I shall do for you, before I am taken from you.” And Elisha said, “Please let there be a double portion of your spirit on me.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And he said, “You have asked a hard thing; yet, if you see me as I am being taken from you, it shall be so for you, but if you do not see me, it shall not be so.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And as they still went on and talked, behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9563O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9563O\"></sup>chariots of fire and horses of fire separated the two of them. And Elijah went up by a whirlwind into heaven.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And Elisha saw it and he cried, “My father, my father! <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9564P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9564P\"></sup>The chariots of Israel and its horsemen!” And he saw him no more.Then he took hold of his own clothes <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9564Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9564Q\"></sup>and tore them in two pieces.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And he took up the cloak of Elijah that had fallen from him and went back and stood on the bank of the Jordan.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then he took the cloak of Elijah that had fallen from him and struck the water, saying, “Where is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Elijah?” And when he had struck the water, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9566R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9566R\"></sup>the water was parted to the one side and to the other, and Elisha went over.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Now when <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9567S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9567S\"></sup>the sons of the prophets who were at Jericho saw him opposite them, they said, “The spirit of Elijah rests on Elisha.” And they came to meet him and bowed to the ground before him.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And they said to him, “Behold now, there are with your servants fifty strong men. Please let them go and seek your master. It may be that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9568T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9568T\"></sup>the Spirit of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has caught him up and cast him upon some mountain or into some valley.” And he said, “You shall not send.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>But when they urged him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9569U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9569U\"></sup>till he was ashamed, he said, “Send.” They sent therefore fifty men. And for three days they sought him but did not find him.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And they came back to him while he was staying at Jericho, and he said to them, “Did I not say to you, ‘Do not go’?”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Now the men of the city said to Elisha, “Behold, the situation of this city is pleasant, as my lord sees, but the water is bad, and the land is unfruitful.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>He said, “Bring me a new bowl, and put salt in it.” So they brought it to him.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then he went to the spring of water and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9573V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9573V\"></sup>threw salt in it and said, “Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, I have healed this water; from now on neither death nor miscarriage shall come from it.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>So the water has been healed to this day, according to the word that Elisha spoke.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>He went up from there to Bethel, and while he was going up on the way, some small boys came out of the city and jeered at him, saying, “Go up, you baldhead! Go up, you baldhead!”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And he turned around, and when he saw them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9576W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9576W\"></sup>he cursed them in the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. And two she-bears came out of the woods and tore forty-two of the boys.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>From there he went on to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9577X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9577X\"></sup>Mount Carmel, and from there he returned <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9577Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9577Y\"></sup>to Samaria."
		},
		"3": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">3 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9578A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9578A\"></sup>In the eighteenth year of Jehoshaphat king of Judah, Jehoram the son of Ahab became king over Israel in Samaria, and he reigned twelve years.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He did what was evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, though not like his father and mother, for he put away the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9579B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9579B\"></sup>pillar of Baal <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9579C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9579C\"></sup>that his father had made.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Nevertheless, he clung to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9580D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9580D\"></sup>the sin of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9580E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9580E\"></sup>which he made Israel to sin; he did not depart from it.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Now Mesha king of Moab was a sheep breeder, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9581F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9581F\"></sup>and he had to deliver to the king of Israel 100,000 lambs and the wool of 100,000 rams.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9582G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9582G\"></sup>when Ahab died, the king of Moab rebelled against the king of Israel.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So King Jehoram marched out of Samaria at that time and mustered all Israel.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And he went and sent word to Jehoshaphat king of Judah: “The king of Moab has rebelled against me. Will you go with me to battle against Moab?” And he said, “I will go. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9584H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9584H\"></sup>I am as you are, my people as your people, my horses as your horses.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then he said, “By which way shall we march?” Jehoram answered, “By the way of the wilderness of Edom.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>So the king of Israel went with the king of Judah and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9586I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9586I\"></sup>the king of Edom. And when they had made a circuitous march of seven days, there was no water for the army or for the animals that followed them.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then the king of Israel said, “Alas! <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9587J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9587J\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has called these three kings to give them into the hand of Moab.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9588K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9588K\"></sup>And Jehoshaphat said, “Is there no prophet of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> here, through whom we may inquire of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>?” Then one of the king of Israel's servants answered, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9588L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9588L\"></sup>“Elisha the son of Shaphat is here, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9588M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9588M\"></sup>who poured water on the hands of Elijah.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And Jehoshaphat said, “The word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is with him.” So the king of Israel and Jehoshaphat and the king of Edom went down to him.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And Elisha said to the king of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9590N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9590N\"></sup>“What have I to do with you? Go to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9590O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9590O\"></sup>the prophets of your father and to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9590P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9590P\"></sup>the prophets of your mother.” But the king of Israel said to him, “No; it is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9590Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9590Q\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> who has called these three kings to give them into the hand of Moab.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And Elisha said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9591R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9591R\"></sup>“As the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> of hosts lives, before whom I stand, were it not that I have regard for Jehoshaphat the king of Judah, I would neither look at you nor see you.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>But now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9592S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9592S\"></sup>bring me a musician.” And when the musician played, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9592T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9592T\"></sup>the hand of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came upon him.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And he said, “Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, ‘I will make this dry streambed full of pools.’",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>For thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, ‘You shall not see wind or rain, but that streambed shall be filled with water, so that you shall drink, you, your livestock, and your animals.’",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>This is a light thing in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. He will also give the Moabites into your hand,",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>and you shall attack every fortified city and every choice city, and shall fell every good tree and stop up all springs of water <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9596U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9596U\"></sup>and ruin every good piece of land with stones.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The next morning, about the time of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9597V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9597V\"></sup>offering the sacrifice, behold, water came from the direction of Edom, till the country was filled with water.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>When all the Moabites heard that the kings had come up to fight against them, all who were able to put on armor, from the youngest to the oldest, were called out and were drawn up at the border.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And when they rose early in the morning and the sun shone on the water, the Moabites saw the water opposite them as red as blood.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And they said, “This is blood; the kings have surely fought together and struck one another down. Now then, Moab, to the spoil!”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>But when they came to the camp of Israel, the Israelites rose and struck the Moabites, till they fled before them. And they went forward, striking the Moabites as they went.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And they overthrew the cities, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9602W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9602W\"></sup>on every good piece of land every man threw a stone until it was covered. They stopped every spring of water and felled all the good trees, till only its stones were left in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9602X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9602X\"></sup>Kir-hareseth, and the slingers surrounded and attacked it.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>When the king of Moab saw that the battle was going against him, he took with him 700 <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9603Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9603Y\"></sup>swordsmen to break through, opposite the king of Edom, but they could not.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Then he took his oldest son who was to reign in his place <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9604Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9604Z\"></sup>and offered him for a burnt offering on the wall. And there came great wrath against Israel. And they withdrew from him and returned to their own land."
		},
		"4": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">4 </span>Now the wife of one of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9605A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9605A\"></sup>sons of the prophets cried to Elisha, “Your servant my husband is dead, and you know that your servant feared the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9605B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9605B\"></sup>but the creditor has come to take my two children to be his slaves.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And Elisha said to her, “What shall I do for you? Tell me; what have you in the house?” And she said, “Your servant has nothing in the house except a jar of oil.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then he said, “Go outside, borrow vessels from all your neighbors, empty vessels and not too few.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then go in and shut the door behind yourself and your sons and pour into all these vessels. And when one is full, set it aside.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>So she went from him and shut the door behind herself and her sons. And as she poured they brought the vessels to her.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>When the vessels were full, she said to her son, “Bring me another vessel.” And he said to her, “There is not another.” Then the oil stopped flowing.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>She came and told the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9611C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9611C\"></sup>man of God, and he said, “Go, sell the oil and pay your debts, and you and your sons can live on the rest.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>One day Elisha went on to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9612D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9612D\"></sup>Shunem, where a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9612E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9612E\"></sup>wealthy woman lived, who urged him to eat some food. So whenever he passed that way, he would turn in there to eat food.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And she said to her husband, “Behold now, I know that this is a holy <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9613F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9613F\"></sup>man of God who is continually passing our way.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Let us make a small room on the roof with walls and put there for him a bed, a table, a chair, and a lamp, so that whenever he comes to us, he can go in there.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>One day he came there, and he turned into the chamber and rested there.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And he said to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9616G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9616G\"></sup>Gehazi his servant, “Call this Shunammite.” When he had called her, she stood before him.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And he said to him, “Say now to her, ‘See, you have taken all this trouble for us; what is to be done for you? Would you have a word spoken on your behalf to the king or to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9617H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9617H\"></sup>the commander of the army?’” She answered, “I dwell among my own people.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And he said, “What then is to be done for her?” Gehazi answered, “Well, she has no son, and her husband is old.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>He said, “Call her.” And when he had called her, she stood in the doorway.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And he said, “At this season, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9620I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9620I\"></sup>about this time next year, you shall embrace a son.” And she said, “No, my lord, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9620J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9620J\"></sup>O man of God; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9620K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9620K\"></sup>do not lie to your servant.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>But the woman conceived, and she bore a son about that time <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9621L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9621L\"></sup>the following spring, as Elisha had said to her.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>When the child had grown, he went out one day to his father among the reapers.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And he said to his father, “Oh, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9623M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9623M\"></sup>my head, my head!” The father said to his servant, “Carry him to his mother.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And when he had lifted him and brought him to his mother, the child sat on her lap till noon, and then he died.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And she went up <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9625N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9625N\"></sup>and laid him on the bed of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9625O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9625O\"></sup>man of God and shut the door behind him and went out.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then she called to her husband and said, “Send me one of the servants and one of the donkeys, that I may quickly go to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9626P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9626P\"></sup>the man of God and come back again.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And he said, “Why will you go to him today? It is neither <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9627Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9627Q\"></sup>new moon nor Sabbath.” She said, “All is well.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then she saddled the donkey, and she said to her servant, “Urge the animal on; do not slacken the pace for me unless I tell you.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>So she set out and came to the man of God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9629R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9629R\"></sup>at Mount Carmel.When the man of God saw her coming, he said to Gehazi his servant, “Look, there is the Shunammite.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Run at once to meet her and say to her, ‘Is all well with you? Is all well with your husband? Is all well with the child?’” And she answered, “All is well.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And when she came <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9631S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9631S\"></sup>to the mountain to the man of God, she caught hold of his feet. And Gehazi came to push her away. But the man of God said, “Leave her alone, for she is in bitter distress, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has hidden it from me and has not told me.”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Then she said, “Did I ask my lord for a son? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9632T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9632T\"></sup>Did I not say, ‘Do not deceive me?’”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>He said to Gehazi, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9633U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9633U\"></sup>“Tie up your garment and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9633V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9633V\"></sup>take my staff in your hand and go. If you meet anyone, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9633W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9633W\"></sup>do not greet him, and if anyone greets you, do not reply. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9633X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9633X\"></sup>lay my staff on the face of the child.”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Then the mother of the child said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9634Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9634Y\"></sup>“As the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives and as you yourself live, I will not leave you.” So he arose and followed her.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Gehazi went on ahead and laid the staff on the face of the child, but there was no sound or sign of life. Therefore he returned to meet him and told him, “The child <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9635Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9635Z\"></sup>has not awakened.”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>When Elisha came into the house, he saw the child lying dead on his bed.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>So he went in and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9637AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9637AA\"></sup>shut the door behind the two of them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9637AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9637AB\"></sup>and prayed to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Then he went up and lay on the child, putting his mouth on his mouth, his eyes on his eyes, and his hands on his hands. And as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9638AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9638AC\"></sup>he stretched himself upon him, the flesh of the child became warm.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Then he got up again and walked once back and forth in the house, and went up <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9639AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9639AD\"></sup>and stretched himself upon him. The child sneezed seven times, and the child opened his eyes.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Then he summoned Gehazi and said, “Call this Shunammite.” So he called her. And when she came to him, he said, “Pick up your son.”",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>She came and fell at his feet, bowing to the ground. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9641AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9641AE\"></sup>Then she picked up her son and went out.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>And Elisha came again to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9642AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9642AF\"></sup>Gilgal when <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9642AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9642AG\"></sup>there was a famine in the land. And as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9642AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9642AH\"></sup>the sons of the prophets <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9642AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9642AI\"></sup>were sitting before him, he said to his servant, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9642AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9642AJ\"></sup>“Set on the large pot, and boil stew for the sons of the prophets.”",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>One of them went out into the field to gather herbs, and found a wild vine and gathered from it his lap full of wild gourds, and came and cut them up into the pot of stew, not knowing what they were.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>And they poured out some for the men to eat. But while they were eating of the stew, they cried out, “O man of God, there is death in the pot!” And they could not eat it.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>He said, “Then bring flour.” <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9645AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9645AK\"></sup>And he threw it into the pot and said, “Pour some out for the men, that they may eat.” And there was no harm in the pot.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>A man came from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9646AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9646AL\"></sup>Baal-shalishah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9646AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9646AM\"></sup>bringing the man of God bread of the firstfruits, twenty loaves of barley and fresh ears of grain in his sack. And Elisha said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9646AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9646AN\"></sup>“Give to the men, that they may eat.”",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>But his servant said, “How can I set this before a hundred men?” So he repeated, “Give them to the men, that they may eat, for thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, ‘They shall eat and have some left.’”",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>So he set it before them. And they ate and had some left, according to the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>."
		},
		"5": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">5 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9649A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9649A\"></sup>Naaman, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9649B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9649B\"></sup>commander of the army of the king of Syria, was a great man with his master and in high favor, because by him the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had given victory to Syria. He was a mighty man of valor, but he was a leper.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Now the Syrians on <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9650C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9650C\"></sup>one of their raids had carried off a little girl from the land of Israel, and she worked in the service of Naaman's wife.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>She said to her mistress, “Would that my lord were with the prophet who is in Samaria! He would cure him of his leprosy.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So Naaman went in and told his lord, “Thus and so spoke the girl from the land of Israel.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And the king of Syria said, “Go now, and I will send a letter to the king of Israel.”So he went, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9653D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9653D\"></sup>taking with him ten talents of silver, six thousand shekels of gold, and ten <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9653E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9653E\"></sup>changes of clothing.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And he brought the letter to the king of Israel, which read, “When this letter reaches you, know that I have sent to you Naaman my servant, that you may cure him of his leprosy.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And when the king of Israel read the letter, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9655F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9655F\"></sup>he tore his clothes and said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9655G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9655G\"></sup>“Am I God, to kill and to make alive, that this man sends word to me to cure a man of his leprosy? Only <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9655H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9655H\"></sup>consider, and see how he is seeking a quarrel with me.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But when Elisha the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9656I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9656I\"></sup>man of God heard that the king of Israel had torn his clothes, he sent to the king, saying, “Why have you torn your clothes? Let him come now to me, that he may know that there is a prophet in Israel.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>So Naaman came with his horses and chariots and stood at the door of Elisha's house.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And Elisha sent a messenger to him, saying, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9658J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9658J\"></sup>“Go and wash in the Jordan seven times, and your flesh shall be restored, and you shall be clean.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>But Naaman was angry and went away, saying, “Behold, I thought that he would surely come out to me and stand and call upon the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God, and wave his hand over the place and cure the leper.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Are not Abana and Pharpar, the rivers of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9660K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9660K\"></sup>Damascus, better than all the waters of Israel? Could I not wash in them and be clean?” So he turned and went away in a rage.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>But his servants came near and said to him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9661L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9661L\"></sup>“My father, it is a great word the prophet has spoken to you; will you not do it? Has he actually said to you, ‘Wash, and be clean’?”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>So he went down and dipped himself seven times in the Jordan, according to the word of the man of God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9662M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9662M\"></sup>and his flesh was restored like the flesh of a little child, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9662N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9662N\"></sup>and he was clean.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then he returned to the man of God, he and all his company, and he came and stood before him. And he said, “Behold, I know that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9663O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9663O\"></sup>there is no God in all the earth but in Israel; so <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9663P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9663P\"></sup>accept now a present from your servant.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>But he said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9664Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9664Q\"></sup>“As the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives, before whom I stand, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9664R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9664R\"></sup>I will receive none.” And he urged him to take it, but he refused.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then Naaman said, “If not, please let there be given to your servant two mule loads of earth, for from now on your servant will not offer burnt offering or sacrifice to any god but the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>In this matter may the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> pardon your servant: when my master goes into the house of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9666S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9666S\"></sup>Rimmon to worship there, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9666T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9666T\"></sup>leaning on my arm, and I bow myself in the house of Rimmon, when I bow myself in the house of Rimmon, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> pardon your servant in this matter.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>He said to him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9667U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9667U\"></sup>“Go in peace.”But when Naaman had gone from him a short distance,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9668V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9668V\"></sup>Gehazi, the servant of Elisha the man of God, said, “See, my master has spared this Naaman the Syrian, in not accepting from his hand what he brought. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9668W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9668W\"></sup>As the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives, I will run after him and get something from him.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>So Gehazi followed Naaman. And when Naaman saw someone running after him, he got down from the chariot to meet him and said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9669X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9669X\"></sup>“Is all well?”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And he said, “All is well. My master has sent me to say, ‘There have just now come to me from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9670Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9670Y\"></sup>the hill country of Ephraim two young men of the sons of the prophets. Please give them a talent of silver and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9670Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9670Z\"></sup>two changes of clothing.’”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And Naaman said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9671AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9671AA\"></sup>“Be pleased to accept two talents.” And he urged him and tied up two talents of silver in two bags, with two changes of clothing, and laid them on two of his servants. And they carried them before Gehazi.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And when he came to the hill, he took them from their hand and put them in the house, and he sent the men away, and they departed.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>He went in and stood before his master, and Elisha said to him, “Where have you been, Gehazi?” And he said, “Your servant went nowhere.”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>But he said to him, “Did not my heart go when the man turned from his chariot to meet you? Was it a time to accept money and garments, olive orchards and vineyards, sheep and oxen, male servants and female servants?",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Therefore the leprosy of Naaman shall cling to you and to your descendants forever.” So he went out from his presence <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9675AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9675AB\"></sup>a leper, like snow."
		},
		"6": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">6 </span>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9676A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9676A\"></sup>the sons of the prophets said to Elisha, “See, the place where we dwell under your charge is too small for us.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Let us go to the Jordan and each of us get there a log, and let us make a place for us to dwell there.” And he answered, “Go.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then one of them said, “Be pleased to go with your servants.” And he answered, “I will go.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So he went with them. And when they came to the Jordan, they cut down trees.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>But as one was felling a log, his axe head fell into the water, and he cried out, “Alas, my master! It was borrowed.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then the man of God said, “Where did it fall?” When he showed him the place, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9681B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9681B\"></sup>he cut off a stick and threw it in there and made the iron float.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And he said, “Take it up.” So he reached out his hand and took it.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Once when the king of Syria was warring against Israel, he took counsel with his servants, saying, “At such and such a place shall be my camp.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But the man of God sent word to the king of Israel, “Beware that you do not pass this place, for the Syrians are going down there.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And the king of Israel sent to the place about which the man of God told him. Thus he used to warn him, so that he saved himself there more than once or twice.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And the mind of the king of Syria was greatly troubled because of this thing, and he called his servants and said to them, “Will you not show me who of us is for the king of Israel?”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And one of his servants said, “None, my lord, O king; but Elisha, the prophet who is in Israel, tells the king of Israel the words that you speak in your bedroom.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And he said, “Go and see where he is, that I may send and seize him.” It was told him, “Behold, he is in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9688C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9688C\"></sup>Dothan.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>So he sent there horses and chariots and a great army, and they came by night and surrounded the city.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>When the servant of the man of God rose early in the morning and went out, behold, an army with horses and chariots was all around the city. And the servant said, “Alas, my master! What shall we do?”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>He said, “Do not be afraid, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9691D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9691D\"></sup>for those who are with us are more than those who are with them.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then Elisha prayed and said, “O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, please <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9692E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9692E\"></sup>open his eyes that he may see.” So the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> opened the eyes of the young man, and he saw, and behold, the mountain was full of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9692F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9692F\"></sup>horses and chariots of fire all around Elisha.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And when the Syrians came down against him, Elisha prayed to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and said, “Please strike this people with blindness.” <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9693G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9693G\"></sup>So he struck them with blindness in accordance with the prayer of Elisha.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And Elisha said to them, “This is not the way, and this is not the city. Follow me, and I will bring you to the man whom you seek.” And he led them to Samaria.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>As soon as they entered Samaria, Elisha said, “O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9695H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9695H\"></sup>open the eyes of these men, that they may see.” So the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> opened their eyes and they saw, and behold, they were in the midst of Samaria.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>As soon as the king of Israel saw them, he said to Elisha, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9696I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9696I\"></sup>“My father, shall I strike them down? Shall I strike them down?”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>He answered, “You shall not strike them down. Would you strike down those whom you have taken captive <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9697J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9697J\"></sup>with your sword and with your bow? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9697K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9697K\"></sup>Set bread and water before them, that they may eat and drink and go to their master.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>So he prepared for them a great feast, and when they had eaten and drunk, he sent them away, and they went to their master. And the Syrians did not come again <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9698L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9698L\"></sup>on raids into the land of Israel.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Afterward <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9699M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9699M\"></sup>Ben-hadad king of Syria mustered his entire army and went up and besieged Samaria.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And there was a great famine in Samaria, as they besieged it, until a donkey's head was sold for eighty shekels of silver, and the fourth part of a kab of dove's dung for five shekels of silver.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Now as the king of Israel was passing by on the wall, a woman cried out to him, saying, “Help, my lord, O king!”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And he said, “If the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will not help you, how shall I help you? From the threshing floor, or from the winepress?”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>And the king asked her, “What is your trouble?” She answered, “This woman said to me, ‘Give your son, that we may eat him today, and we will eat my son tomorrow.’",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9704N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9704N\"></sup>So we boiled my son and ate him. And on the next day I said to her, ‘Give your son, that we may eat him.’ But she has hidden her son.”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>When the king heard the words of the woman, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9705O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9705O\"></sup>he tore his clothes—now he was passing by on the wall—and the people looked, and behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9705P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9705P\"></sup>he had sackcloth beneath on his body—",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>and he said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9706Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9706Q\"></sup>“May God do so to me and more also, if the head of Elisha the son of Shaphat remains on his shoulders today.”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Elisha was sitting in his house, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9707R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9707R\"></sup>and the elders were sitting with him. Now the king had dispatched a man from his presence, but before the messenger arrived Elisha said to the elders, “Do you see how this <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9707S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9707S\"></sup>murderer has sent to take off my head? Look, when the messenger comes, shut the door and hold the door fast against him. Is not the sound of his master's feet behind him?”",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>And while he was still speaking with them, the messenger came down to him and said, “This trouble is from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>! <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9708T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9708T\"></sup>Why should I wait for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> any longer?”"
		},
		"7": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">7 </span>But Elisha said, “Hear the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>: thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9709A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9709A\"></sup>Tomorrow about this time a seah of fine flour shall be sold for a shekel, and two seahs of barley for a shekel, at the gate of Samaria.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9710B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9710B\"></sup>the captain on whose hand the king leaned said to the man of God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9710C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9710C\"></sup>“If the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> himself should make windows in heaven, could this thing be?” But he said, “You shall see it with your own eyes, but you shall not eat of it.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Now there were four men who were lepers <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9711D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9711D\"></sup>at the entrance to the gate. And they said to one another, “Why are we sitting here until we die?",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>If we say, ‘Let us enter the city,’ the famine is in the city, and we shall die there. And if we sit here, we die also. So now come, let us go over to the camp of the Syrians. If they spare our lives we shall live, and if they kill us we shall but die.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>So they arose at twilight to go to the camp of the Syrians. But when they came to the edge of the camp of the Syrians, behold, there was no one there.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>For the Lord had made the army of the Syrians <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9714E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9714E\"></sup>hear the sound of chariots and of horses, the sound of a great army, so that they said to one another, “Behold, the king of Israel has hired against us <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9714F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9714F\"></sup>the kings of the Hittites and the kings of Egypt to come against us.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9715G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9715G\"></sup>So they fled away in the twilight and abandoned their tents, their horses, and their donkeys, leaving the camp as it was, and fled for their lives.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And when these lepers came to the edge of the camp, they went into a tent and ate and drank, and they carried off silver and gold and clothing and went and hid them. Then they came back and entered another tent and carried off things from it and went and hid them.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then they said to one another, “We are not doing right. This day is a day of good news. If we are silent and wait until the morning light, punishment will overtake us. Now therefore come; let us go and tell the king's household.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>So they came and called to the gatekeepers of the city and told them, “We came to the camp of the Syrians, and behold, there was no one to be seen or heard there, nothing but the horses tied and the donkeys tied and the tents as they were.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then the gatekeepers called out, and it was told within the king's household.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And the king rose in the night and said to his servants, “I will tell you what the Syrians have done to us. They know that we are hungry. Therefore they have gone out of the camp to hide themselves in the open country, thinking, ‘When they come out of the city, we shall take them alive and get into the city.’”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And one of his servants said, “Let some men take five of the remaining horses, seeing that those who are left here will fare like the whole multitude of Israel who have already perished. Let us send and see.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>So they took two horsemen, and the king sent them after the army of the Syrians, saying, “Go and see.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>So they went after them as far as the Jordan, and behold, all the way was littered with garments and equipment that the Syrians had thrown away in their haste. And the messengers returned and told the king.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then the people went out and plundered the camp of the Syrians. So a seah of fine flour was sold for a shekel, and two seahs of barley for a shekel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9724H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9724H\"></sup>according to the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Now the king had appointed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9725I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9725I\"></sup>the captain on whose hand he leaned to have charge of the gate. And the people trampled him in the gate, so that he died, as the man of God had said <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9725J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9725J\"></sup>when the king came down to him.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>For when the man of God had said to the king, “Two seahs of barley shall be sold for a shekel, and a seah of fine flour for a shekel, about this time tomorrow in the gate of Samaria,”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9727K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9727K\"></sup>the captain had answered the man of God, “If the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> himself should make windows in heaven, could such a thing be?” And he had said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9727L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9727L\"></sup>“You shall see it with your own eyes, but you shall not eat of it.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And so it happened to him, for the people trampled him in the gate and he died."
		},
		"8": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">8 </span>Now Elisha had said to the woman <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9729A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9729A\"></sup>whose son he had restored to life, “Arise, and depart with your household, and sojourn wherever you can, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9729B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9729B\"></sup>has called for a famine, and it will come upon the land for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9729C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9729C\"></sup>seven years.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>So the woman arose and did according to the word of the man of God. She went with her household and sojourned in the land of the Philistines seven years.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And at the end of the seven years, when the woman returned from the land of the Philistines, she went to appeal to the king for her house and her land.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Now the king was talking with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9732D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9732D\"></sup>Gehazi the servant of the man of God, saying, “Tell me all the great things that Elisha has done.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And while he was telling the king how <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9733E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9733E\"></sup>Elisha had restored the dead to life, behold, the woman whose son he had restored to life appealed to the king for her house and her land. And Gehazi said, “My lord, O king, here is the woman, and here is her son whom Elisha restored to life.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And when the king asked the woman, she told him. So the king appointed an official for her, saying, “Restore all that was hers, together with all the produce of the fields from the day that she left the land until now.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Now Elisha came to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9735F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9735F\"></sup>Damascus. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9735G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9735G\"></sup>Ben-hadad the king of Syria was sick. And when it was told him, “The man of God has come here,”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>the king said to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9736H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9736H\"></sup>Hazael, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9736I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9736I\"></sup>“Take a present with you and go to meet the man of God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9736J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9736J\"></sup>and inquire of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> through him, saying, ‘Shall I recover from this sickness?’”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>So Hazael went to meet him, and took a present with him, all kinds of goods of Damascus, forty camels' loads. When he came and stood before him, he said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9737K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9737K\"></sup>“Your son Ben-hadad king of Syria has sent me to you, saying, ‘Shall I recover from this sickness?’”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And Elisha said to him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9738L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9738L\"></sup>“Go, say to him, ‘You shall certainly recover,’ but the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has shown me that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9738M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9738M\"></sup>he shall certainly die.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And he fixed his gaze and stared at him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9739N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9739N\"></sup>until he was embarrassed. And the man of God wept.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And Hazael said, “Why does my lord weep?” He answered, “Because I know <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9740O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9740O\"></sup>the evil that you will do to the people of Israel. You will set on fire their fortresses, and you will kill their young men with the sword <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9740P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9740P\"></sup>and dash in pieces their little ones and rip open their pregnant women.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And Hazael said, “What is your servant, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9741Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9741Q\"></sup>who is but a dog, that he should do this great thing?” Elisha answered, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9741R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9741R\"></sup>“The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has shown me that you are to be king over Syria.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then he departed from Elisha and came to his master, who said to him, “What did Elisha say to you?” And he answered, “He told me <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9742S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9742S\"></sup>that you would certainly recover.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>But the next day he took the bed cloth and dipped it in water and spread it over his face, till he died. And Hazael became king in his place.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>In the fifth year of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9744T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9744T\"></sup>Joram the son of Ahab, king of Israel, when Jehoshaphat was king of Judah, Jehoram the son of Jehoshaphat, king of Judah, began to reign.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>He was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9745U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9745U\"></sup>thirty-two years old when he became king, and he reigned eight years in Jerusalem.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And he walked in the way of the kings of Israel, as the house of Ahab had done, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9746V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9746V\"></sup>the daughter of Ahab was his wife. And he did what was evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Yet the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was not willing to destroy Judah, for the sake of David his servant, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9747W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9747W\"></sup>since he promised to give <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9747X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9747X\"></sup>a lamp to him and to his sons forever.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>In his days Edom revolted from the rule of Judah and set up <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9748Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9748Y\"></sup>a king of their own.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then Joram passed over to Zair with all his chariots and rose by night, and he and his chariot commanders struck the Edomites who had surrounded him, but his army <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9749Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9749Z\"></sup>fled home.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9750AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9750AA\"></sup>So Edom revolted from the rule of Judah to this day. Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9750AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9750AB\"></sup>Libnah revolted at the same time.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Now the rest of the acts of Joram, and all that he did, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Judah?",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>So Joram slept with his fathers and was buried <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9752AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9752AC\"></sup>with his fathers in the city of David, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9752AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9752AD\"></sup>Ahaziah his son reigned in his place.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9753AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9753AE\"></sup>In the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9753AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9753AF\"></sup>twelfth year of Joram the son of Ahab, king of Israel, Ahaziah the son of Jehoram, king of Judah, began to reign.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Ahaziah was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9754AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9754AG\"></sup>twenty-two years old when he began to reign, and he reigned one year in Jerusalem. His mother's name was Athaliah; she was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9754AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9754AH\"></sup>a granddaughter of Omri king of Israel.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>He also walked in the way of the house of Ahab and did what was evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, as the house of Ahab had done, for he was son-in-law to the house of Ahab.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>He went with Joram the son of Ahab to make war against <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9756AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9756AI\"></sup>Hazael king of Syria at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9756AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9756AJ\"></sup>Ramoth-gilead, and the Syrians wounded Joram.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9757AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9757AK\"></sup>And King Joram returned to be healed in Jezreel of the wounds that the Syrians had given him at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9757AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9757AL\"></sup>Ramah, when he fought against Hazael king of Syria. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9757AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9757AM\"></sup>Ahaziah the son of Jehoram king of Judah went down to see Joram the son of Ahab in Jezreel, because he was sick."
		},
		"9": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">9 </span>Then Elisha the prophet called one of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9758A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9758A\"></sup>the sons of the prophets and said to him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9758B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9758B\"></sup>“Tie up your garments, and take this <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9758C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9758C\"></sup>flask of oil in your hand, and go to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9758D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9758D\"></sup>Ramoth-gilead.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And when you arrive, look there for Jehu <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9759E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9759E\"></sup>the son of Jehoshaphat, son of Nimshi. And go in and have him rise from among <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9759F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9759F\"></sup>his fellows, and lead him to an inner chamber.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then take the flask of oil and pour it on his head and say, ‘Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9760G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9760G\"></sup>I anoint you king over Israel.’ Then open the door and flee; do not linger.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So the young man, the servant of the prophet, went to Ramoth-gilead.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And when he came, behold, the commanders of the army were in council. And he said, “I have a word for you, O commander.” And Jehu said, “To which of us all?” And he said, “To you, O commander.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So he arose and went into the house. And the young man poured the oil on his head, saying to him, “Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9763H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9763H\"></sup>I anoint you king over the people of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, over Israel.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And you shall strike down the house of Ahab your master, so that I may avenge <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9764I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9764I\"></sup>on Jezebel the blood of my servants the prophets, and the blood of all the servants of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>For the whole house of Ahab shall perish, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9765J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9765J\"></sup>and I will cut off from Ahab <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9765K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9765K\"></sup>every male, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9765L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9765L\"></sup>bond or free, in Israel.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And I will make the house of Ahab like <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9766M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9766M\"></sup>the house of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, and like <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9766N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9766N\"></sup>the house of Baasha the son of Ahijah.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9767O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9767O\"></sup>And the dogs shall eat Jezebel in the territory of Jezreel, and none shall bury her.” Then he opened the door and fled.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>When Jehu came out to the servants of his master, they said to him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9768P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9768P\"></sup>“Is all well? Why did <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9768Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9768Q\"></sup>this mad fellow come to you?” And he said to them, “You know the fellow and his talk.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And they said, “That is not true; tell us now.” And he said, “Thus and so he spoke to me, saying, ‘Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, I anoint you king over Israel.’”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then in haste <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9770R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9770R\"></sup>every man of them took his garment and put it under him on the bare steps, and they blew the trumpet and proclaimed, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9770S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9770S\"></sup>“Jehu is king.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Thus Jehu the son of Jehoshaphat the son of Nimshi conspired against Joram. (<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9771T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9771T\"></sup>Now Joram with all Israel had been on guard at Ramoth-gilead against <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9771U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9771U\"></sup>Hazael king of Syria,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9772V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9772V\"></sup>but King Joram had returned to be healed in Jezreel of the wounds that the Syrians had given him, when he fought with Hazael king of Syria.) So Jehu said, “If this is your decision, then let no one slip out of the city to go and tell the news in Jezreel.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then Jehu mounted his chariot and went to Jezreel, for Joram lay there. And Ahaziah king of Judah had come down to visit Joram.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Now the watchman was standing on the tower in Jezreel, and he saw the company of Jehu as he came and said, “I see a company.” And Joram said, “Take a horseman and send to meet them, and let him say, ‘Is it peace?’”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>So a man on horseback went to meet him and said, “Thus says the king, ‘Is it peace?’” And Jehu said, “What do you have to do with peace? Turn around and ride behind me.” And the watchman reported, saying, “The messenger reached them, but he is not coming back.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Then he sent out a second horseman, who came to them and said, “Thus the king has said, ‘Is it peace?’” And Jehu answered, “What do you have to do with peace? Turn around and ride behind me.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Again the watchman reported, “He reached them, but he is not coming back. And the driving <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9777W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9777W\"></sup>is like the driving of Jehu <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9777X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9777X\"></sup>the son of Nimshi, for he drives furiously.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Joram said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9778Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9778Y\"></sup>“Make ready.” And they made ready his chariot. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9778Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9778Z\"></sup>Then Joram king of Israel and Ahaziah king of Judah set out, each in his chariot, and went to meet Jehu, and met him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9778AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9778AA\"></sup>at the property of Naboth the Jezreelite.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And when Joram saw Jehu, he said, “Is it peace, Jehu?” He answered, “What peace can there be, so long as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9779AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9779AB\"></sup>the whorings and the sorceries of your mother Jezebel are so many?”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Then Joram reined about and fled, saying to Ahaziah, “Treachery, O Ahaziah!”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And Jehu drew his bow with his full strength, and shot Joram between the shoulders, so that the arrow pierced his heart, and he sank in his chariot.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Jehu said to Bidkar <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9782AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9782AC\"></sup>his aide, “Take him up and throw him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9782AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9782AD\"></sup>on the plot of ground belonging to Naboth the Jezreelite. For remember, when you and I rode side by side behind Ahab his father, how <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9782AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9782AE\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> made this <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9782AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9782AF\"></sup>pronouncement against him:",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>‘As surely as I saw yesterday the blood of Naboth and the blood of his sons—declares the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>—I will repay you on this plot of ground.’ Now therefore take him up and throw him on the plot of ground, in accordance with the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9784AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9784AG\"></sup>When Ahaziah the king of Judah saw this, he fled in the direction of Beth-haggan. And Jehu pursued him and said, “Shoot him also.” And they shot him in the chariot at the ascent of Gur, which is by <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9784AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9784AH\"></sup>Ibleam. And he fled to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9784AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9784AI\"></sup>Megiddo and died there.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9785AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9785AJ\"></sup>His servants carried him in a chariot to Jerusalem, and buried him in his tomb with his fathers in the city of David.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>In the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9786AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9786AK\"></sup>eleventh year of Joram the son of Ahab, Ahaziah began to reign over Judah.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>When Jehu came to Jezreel, Jezebel heard of it. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9787AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9787AL\"></sup>she painted her eyes and adorned her head and looked out of the window.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>And as Jehu entered the gate, she said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9788AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9788AM\"></sup>“Is it peace, you Zimri, murderer of your master?”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>And he lifted up his face to the window and said, “Who is on my side? Who?” Two or three eunuchs looked out at him.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>He said, “Throw her down.” So they threw her down. And some of her blood spattered on the wall and on the horses, and they trampled on her.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Then he went in and ate and drank. And he said, “See now to this cursed woman and bury her, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9791AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9791AN\"></sup>for she is a king's daughter.”",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>But when they went to bury her, they found no more of her than the skull and the feet and the palms of her hands.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>When they came back and told him, he said, “This is the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, which he spoke by his servant Elijah the Tishbite: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9793AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9793AO\"></sup>‘In the territory of Jezreel the dogs shall eat the flesh of Jezebel,",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>and the corpse of Jezebel shall be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9794AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9794AP\"></sup>as dung on the face of the field in the territory of Jezreel, so that no one can say, This is Jezebel.’”"
		},
		"10": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">10 </span>Now Ahab had seventy sons in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9795A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9795A\"></sup>Samaria. So Jehu wrote letters and sent them to Samaria, to the rulers of the city, to the elders, and to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9795B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9795B\"></sup>the guardians of the sons of Ahab, saying,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Now then, as soon as this letter comes to you, seeing your master's sons are with you, and there are with you chariots and horses, fortified cities also, and weapons,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>select the best and fittest of your master's sons and set him on his father's throne and fight for your master's house.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But they were exceedingly afraid and said, “Behold, the two kings could not stand before him. How then can we stand?”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>So he who was over the palace, and he who was over the city, together with the elders and the guardians, sent to Jehu, saying, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9799C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9799C\"></sup>“We are your servants, and we will do all that you tell us. We will not make anyone king. Do whatever is good in your eyes.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then he wrote to them a second letter, saying, “If you are on my side, and if you are ready to obey me, take the heads of your master's sons and come to me at Jezreel tomorrow at this time.” Now the king's sons, seventy persons, were with the great men of the city, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9800D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9800D\"></sup>who were bringing them up.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And as soon as the letter came to them, they took the king's sons <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9801E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9801E\"></sup>and slaughtered them, seventy persons, and put their heads in baskets and sent them to him at Jezreel.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>When the messenger came and told him, “They have brought the heads of the king's sons,” he said, “Lay them in two heaps at the entrance of the gate until the morning.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then in the morning, when he went out, he stood and said to all the people, “You are innocent. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9803F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9803F\"></sup>It was I who conspired against my master and killed him, but who struck down all these?",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Know then that there shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9804G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9804G\"></sup>fall to the earth nothing of the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke concerning the house of Ahab, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has done <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9804H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9804H\"></sup>what he said by his servant Elijah.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>So Jehu struck down all who remained of the house of Ahab in Jezreel, all his great men and his close friends and his priests, until he left him none remaining.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then he set out and went to Samaria. On the way, when he was at Beth-eked of the Shepherds,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Jehu met <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9807I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9807I\"></sup>the relatives of Ahaziah king of Judah, and he said, “Who are you?” And they answered, “We are the relatives of Ahaziah, and we came down to visit the royal princes and the sons of the queen mother.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>He said, “Take them alive.” And they took them alive and slaughtered them at the pit of Beth-eked, forty-two persons, and he spared none of them.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And when he departed from there, he met <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9809J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9809J\"></sup>Jehonadab the son of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9809K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9809K\"></sup>Rechab coming to meet him. And he greeted him and said to him, “Is your heart true to my heart as mine is to yours?” And Jehonadab answered, “It is.” Jehu said, “If it is, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9809L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9809L\"></sup>give me your hand.” So he gave him his hand. And Jehu took him up with him into the chariot.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And he said, “Come with me, and see <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9810M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9810M\"></sup>my zeal for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.” So he had him ride in his chariot.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And when he came to Samaria, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9811N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9811N\"></sup>he struck down all who remained to Ahab in Samaria, till he had wiped them out, according to the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9811O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9811O\"></sup>that he spoke to Elijah.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then Jehu assembled all the people and said to them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9812P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9812P\"></sup>“Ahab served Baal a little, but Jehu will serve him much.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Now therefore call to me all the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9813Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9813Q\"></sup>prophets of Baal, all his worshipers and all his priests. Let none be missing, for I have a great sacrifice to offer to Baal. Whoever is missing shall not live.” But Jehu did it with cunning in order to destroy the worshipers of Baal.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And Jehu ordered, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9814R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9814R\"></sup>“Sanctify <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9814S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9814S\"></sup>a solemn assembly for Baal.” So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9814T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9814T\"></sup>they proclaimed it.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And Jehu sent throughout all Israel, and all the worshipers of Baal came, so that there was not a man left who did not come. And they entered <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9815U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9815U\"></sup>the house of Baal, and the house of Baal was filled from one end to the other.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>He said to him who was in charge of the wardrobe, “Bring out the vestments for all the worshipers of Baal.” So he brought out the vestments for them.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Then Jehu went into the house of Baal with Jehonadab the son of Rechab, and he said to the worshipers of Baal, “Search, and see that there is no servant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> here among you, but only the worshipers of Baal.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then they went in to offer sacrifices and burnt offerings.Now Jehu had stationed eighty men outside and said, “The man who allows any of those whom I give into your hands to escape <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9818V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9818V\"></sup>shall forfeit his life.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>So as soon as he had made an end of offering the burnt offering, Jehu said to the guard and to the officers, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9819W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9819W\"></sup>“Go in and strike them down; let not a man escape.” So when they put them to the sword, the guard and the officers cast them out and went into the inner room of the house of Baal,",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>and they brought out the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9820X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9820X\"></sup>pillar that was in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9820Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9820Y\"></sup>the house of Baal and burned it.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And they demolished the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9821Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9821Z\"></sup>pillar of Baal, and demolished the house of Baal, and made it <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9821AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9821AA\"></sup>a latrine to this day.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Thus Jehu wiped out Baal from Israel.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>But Jehu did not turn aside from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9823AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9823AB\"></sup>the sins of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9823AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9823AC\"></sup>which he made Israel to sin—that is, the golden calves that were in Bethel and in Dan.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Jehu, “Because you have done well in carrying out what is right in my eyes, and have done to the house of Ahab according to all that was in my heart, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9824AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9824AD\"></sup>your sons of the fourth generation shall sit on the throne of Israel.”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>But Jehu was not careful to walk in the law of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, with all his heart. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9825AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9825AE\"></sup>He did not turn from the sins of Jeroboam, which he made Israel to sin.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>In those days the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9826AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9826AF\"></sup>began to cut off parts of Israel. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9826AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9826AG\"></sup>Hazael defeated them throughout the territory of Israel:",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>from the Jordan eastward, all the land of Gilead, the Gadites, and the Reubenites, and the Manassites, from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9827AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9827AH\"></sup>Aroer, which is by the Valley of the Arnon, that is, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9827AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9827AI\"></sup>Gilead and Bashan.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Now the rest of the acts of Jehu and all that he did, and all his might, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel?",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>So Jehu slept with his fathers, and they buried him in Samaria. And Jehoahaz his son reigned in his place.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>The time that Jehu reigned over Israel in Samaria was twenty-eight years."
		},
		"11": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">11 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9831A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9831A\"></sup>Now when <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9831B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9831B\"></sup>Athaliah the mother of Ahaziah saw that her son was dead, she arose and destroyed all the royal family.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>But Jehosheba, the daughter of King Joram, sister of Ahaziah, took <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9832C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9832C\"></sup>Joash the son of Ahaziah and stole him away from among the king's sons who were being put to death, and she put him and his nurse in a bedroom. Thus they hid him from Athaliah, so that he was not put to death.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And he remained with her six years, hidden in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, while Athaliah reigned over the land.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9834D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9834D\"></sup>But in the seventh year <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9834E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9834E\"></sup>Jehoiada sent and brought the captains of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9834F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9834F\"></sup>the Carites and of the guards, and had them come to him in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. And he made a covenant with them and put them under oath in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and he showed them the king's son.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And he commanded them, “This is the thing that you shall do: one third of you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9835G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9835G\"></sup>those who come off duty on the Sabbath and guard the king's house",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>(<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9836H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9836H\"></sup>another third being at the gate Sur and a third at the gate behind the guards) shall guard the palace.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And the two divisions of you, which come on duty in force on the Sabbath and guard the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> on behalf of the king,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>shall surround the king, each with his weapons in his hand. And whoever approaches the ranks is to be put to death. Be with the king <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9838I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9838I\"></sup>when he goes out and when he comes in.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The captains did according to all that Jehoiada the priest commanded, and they each brought his men who were to go off duty on the Sabbath, with those who were to come on duty on the Sabbath, and came to Jehoiada the priest.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And the priest gave to the captains the spears and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9840J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9840J\"></sup>shields that had been King David's, which were in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And the guards stood, every man with his weapons in his hand, from the south side of the house to the north side of the house, around the altar and the house on behalf of the king.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then he brought out the king's son and put <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9842K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9842K\"></sup>the crown on him and gave him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9842L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9842L\"></sup>the testimony. And they proclaimed him king and anointed him, and they clapped their hands and said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9842M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9842M\"></sup>“Long live the king!”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>When Athaliah heard the noise of the guard and of the people, she went into the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to the people.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And when she looked, there was the king standing <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9844N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9844N\"></sup>by the pillar, according to the custom, and the captains and the trumpeters beside the king, and all the people of the land rejoicing and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9844O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9844O\"></sup>blowing trumpets. And Athaliah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9844P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9844P\"></sup>tore her clothes and cried, “Treason! Treason!”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then Jehoiada the priest commanded the captains who were set over the army, “Bring her out between the ranks, and put to death with the sword anyone who follows her.” For the priest said, “Let her not be put to death in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>So they laid hands on her; and she went through the horses' entrance to the king's house, and there she was put to death.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And Jehoiada <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9847Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9847Q\"></sup>made a covenant between the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and the king and people, that they should be the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>'s people, and also <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9847R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9847R\"></sup>between the king and the people.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then all the people of the land went to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9848S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9848S\"></sup>the house of Baal and tore it down; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9848T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9848T\"></sup>his altars and his images they broke in pieces, and they killed Mattan the priest of Baal before the altars. And the priest posted watchmen over the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And he took the captains, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9849U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9849U\"></sup>the Carites, the guards, and all the people of the land, and they brought the king down from the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, marching through <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9849V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9849V\"></sup>the gate of the guards to the king's house. And he took his seat on the throne of the kings.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>So all the people of the land rejoiced, and the city was quiet after Athaliah had been put to death with the sword at the king's house.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9851W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9851W\"></sup>Jehoash was seven years old when he began to reign."
		},
		"12": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">12 </span>In the seventh year of Jehu, Jehoash began to reign, and he reigned forty years in Jerusalem. His mother's name was Zibiah of Beersheba.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And Jehoash did what was right in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> all his days, because Jehoiada the priest instructed him.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Nevertheless, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9854A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9854A\"></sup>the high places were not taken away; the people continued to sacrifice and make offerings on the high places.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Jehoash said to the priests, “All the money of the holy things <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9855B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9855B\"></sup>that is brought into the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the money for which each man is assessed—the money from the assessment of persons—and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9855C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9855C\"></sup>the money that a man's heart prompts him to bring into the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>let the priests take, each from his donor, and let them repair the house wherever any need of repairs is discovered.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>But by the twenty-third year of King Jehoash, the priests had made no repairs on the house.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Therefore King Jehoash summoned Jehoiada the priest and the other priests and said to them, “Why are you not repairing the house? Now therefore take no more money from your donors, but hand it over for the repair of the house.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>So the priests agreed that they should take no more money from the people, and that they should not repair the house.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then Jehoiada the priest took <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9860D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9860D\"></sup>a chest and bored a hole in the lid of it and set it beside the altar on the right side as one entered the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. And the priests who guarded the threshold put in it all the money that was brought into the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And whenever they saw that there was much money in the chest, the king's secretary and the high priest came up and they bagged and counted <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9861E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9861E\"></sup>the money that was found in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then they would give the money that was weighed out into the hands of the workmen who had the oversight of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. And they paid it out to the carpenters and the builders who worked on the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9863F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9863F\"></sup>to the masons and the stonecutters, as well as to buy timber and quarried stone for making repairs on the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and for any outlay for the repairs of the house.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9864G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9864G\"></sup>But there were not made for the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9864H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9864H\"></sup>basins of silver, snuffers, bowls, trumpets, or any vessels of gold, or of silver, from the money that was brought into the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>for that was given to the workmen who were repairing the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> with it.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9866I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9866I\"></sup>they did not ask for an accounting from the men into whose hand they delivered the money to pay out to the workmen, for they dealt honestly.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The money from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9867J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9867J\"></sup>the guilt offerings and the money from the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9867K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9867K\"></sup>sin offerings was not brought into the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9867L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9867L\"></sup>it belonged to the priests.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>At that time <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9868M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9868M\"></sup>Hazael king of Syria went up and fought against Gath and took it. But when Hazael set his face <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9868N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9868N\"></sup>to go up against Jerusalem,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Jehoash king of Judah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9869O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9869O\"></sup>took all the sacred gifts that Jehoshaphat and Jehoram and Ahaziah his fathers, the kings of Judah, had dedicated, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9869P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9869P\"></sup>and his own sacred gifts, and all the gold that was found in the treasuries of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and of the king's house, and sent these to Hazael king of Syria. Then Hazael went away from Jerusalem.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Now the rest of the acts of Joash and all that he did, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Judah?",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9871Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9871Q\"></sup>His servants arose and made a conspiracy <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9871R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9871R\"></sup>and struck down Joash in the house of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9871S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9871S\"></sup>Millo, on the way that goes down to Silla.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>It was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9872T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9872T\"></sup>Jozacar the son of Shimeath and Jehozabad the son of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9872U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9872U\"></sup>Shomer, his servants, who struck him down, so that he died. And they buried him with his fathers in the city of David, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9872V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9872V\"></sup>and Amaziah his son reigned in his place."
		},
		"13": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">13 </span>In the twenty-third year of Joash the son of Ahaziah, king of Judah, Jehoahaz the son of Jehu began to reign over Israel in Samaria, and he reigned seventeen years.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He did what was evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and followed the sins of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9874A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9874A\"></sup>which he made Israel to sin; he did not depart from them.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9875B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9875B\"></sup>And the anger of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was kindled against Israel, and he gave them continually into the hand of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9875C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9875C\"></sup>Hazael king of Syria and into the hand of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9875D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9875D\"></sup>Ben-hadad the son of Hazael.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then Jehoahaz <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9876E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9876E\"></sup>sought the favor of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> listened to him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9876F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9876F\"></sup>for he saw the oppression of Israel, how the king of Syria oppressed them.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>(Therefore the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9877G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9877G\"></sup>a savior, so that they escaped from the hand of the Syrians, and the people of Israel lived in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9877H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9877H\"></sup>their homes as formerly.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Nevertheless, they did not depart from the sins of the house of Jeroboam, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9878I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9878I\"></sup>which he made Israel to sin, but walked in them; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9878J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9878J\"></sup>the Asherah also remained in Samaria.)",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>For there was not left to Jehoahaz an army of more than fifty horsemen and ten chariots and ten thousand footmen, for the king of Syria had destroyed them and made them like the dust <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9879K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9879K\"></sup>at threshing.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Now the rest of the acts of Jehoahaz and all that he did, and his might, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel?",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>So Jehoahaz slept with his fathers, and they buried him in Samaria, and Joash his son reigned in his place.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>In the thirty-seventh year of Joash king of Judah, Jehoash the son of Jehoahaz began to reign over Israel in Samaria, and he reigned sixteen years.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>He also did what was evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. He did not depart from all the sins of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9883L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9883L\"></sup>which he made Israel to sin, but he walked in them.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9884M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9884M\"></sup>Now the rest of the acts of Joash <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9884N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9884N\"></sup>and all that he did, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9884O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9884O\"></sup>and the might with which he fought against Amaziah king of Judah, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel?",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>So Joash slept with his fathers, and Jeroboam sat on his throne. And Joash was buried in Samaria with the kings of Israel.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Now when Elisha had fallen sick with the illness of which he was to die, Joash king of Israel went down to him and wept before him, crying, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9886P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9886P\"></sup>“My father, my father! The chariots of Israel and its horsemen!”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And Elisha said to him, “Take a bow and arrows.” So he took a bow and arrows.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then he said to the king of Israel, “Draw the bow,” and he drew it. And Elisha laid his hands on the king's hands.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And he said, “Open the window eastward,” and he opened it. Then Elisha said, “Shoot,” and he shot. And he said, “The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>'s arrow of victory, the arrow of victory over Syria! For you shall fight the Syrians in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9889Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9889Q\"></sup>Aphek until you have made an end of them.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And he said, “Take the arrows,” and he took them. And he said to the king of Israel, “Strike the ground with them.” And he struck three times and stopped.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9891R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9891R\"></sup>the man of God was angry with him and said, “You should have struck five or six times; then you would have struck down Syria until you had made an end of it, but now you will strike down Syria only <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9891S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9891S\"></sup>three times.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>So Elisha died, and they buried him. Now bands of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9892T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9892T\"></sup>Moabites used to invade the land in the spring of the year.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And as a man was being buried, behold, a marauding band was seen and the man was thrown into the grave of Elisha, and as soon as the man touched the bones of Elisha, he revived and stood on his feet.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9894U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9894U\"></sup>Now Hazael king of Syria oppressed Israel all the days of Jehoahaz.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9895V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9895V\"></sup>But the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was gracious to them and had compassion on them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9895W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9895W\"></sup>and he turned toward them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9895X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9895X\"></sup>because of his covenant with Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob, and would not destroy them, nor has he cast them from his presence until now.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>When Hazael king of Syria died, Ben-hadad his son became king in his place.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Then Jehoash the son of Jehoahaz took again from Ben-hadad the son of Hazael the cities <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9897Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9897Y\"></sup>that he had taken from Jehoahaz his father in war. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9897Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9897Z\"></sup>Three times Joash defeated him and recovered the cities of Israel."
		},
		"14": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">14 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9898A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9898A\"></sup>In the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9898B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9898B\"></sup>second year of Joash the son of Joahaz, king of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9898C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9898C\"></sup>Amaziah the son of Joash, king of Judah, began to reign.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He was twenty-five years old when he began to reign, and he reigned twenty-nine years in Jerusalem. His mother's name was Jehoaddin of Jerusalem.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And he did what was right in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, yet not like David his father. He did in all things as Joash his father had done.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9901D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9901D\"></sup>But the high places were not removed; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9901E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9901E\"></sup>the people still sacrificed and made offerings on the high places.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And as soon as the royal power was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9902F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9902F\"></sup>firmly in his hand, he struck down his servants <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9902G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9902G\"></sup>who had struck down the king his father.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>But he did not put to death the children of the murderers, according to what is written in the Book of the Law of Moses, where the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9903H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9903H\"></sup>“Fathers shall not be put to death because of their children, nor shall children be put to death because of their fathers. But each one shall die for his own sin.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9904I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9904I\"></sup>He struck down ten thousand Edomites in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9904J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9904J\"></sup>the Valley of Salt and took <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9904K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9904K\"></sup>Sela by storm, and called it <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9904L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9904L\"></sup>Joktheel, which is its name to this day.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9905M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9905M\"></sup>Then Amaziah sent messengers to Jehoash the son of Jehoahaz, son of Jehu, king of Israel, saying, “Come, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9905N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9905N\"></sup>let us look one another in the face.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And Jehoash king of Israel sent word to Amaziah king of Judah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9906O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9906O\"></sup>“A thistle on Lebanon sent to a cedar on Lebanon, saying, ‘Give your daughter to my son for a wife,’ and a wild beast of Lebanon passed by and trampled down the thistle.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>You have indeed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9907P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9907P\"></sup>struck down Edom, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9907Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9907Q\"></sup>and your heart has lifted you up. Be content with your glory, and stay at home, for why should you provoke trouble so that you fall, you and Judah with you?”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>But Amaziah would not listen. So Jehoash king of Israel went up, and he and Amaziah king of Judah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9908R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9908R\"></sup>faced one another in battle at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9908S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9908S\"></sup>Beth-shemesh, which belongs to Judah.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And Judah was defeated by Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9909T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9909T\"></sup>and every man fled to his home.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And Jehoash king of Israel captured Amaziah king of Judah, the son of Jehoash, son of Ahaziah, at Beth-shemesh, and came to Jerusalem and broke down the wall of Jerusalem for four hundred cubits, from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9910U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9910U\"></sup>the Ephraim Gate to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9910V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9910V\"></sup>the Corner Gate.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And he seized <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9911W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9911W\"></sup>all the gold and silver, and all the vessels that were found in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and in the treasuries of the king's house, also hostages, and he returned to Samaria.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9912X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9912X\"></sup>Now the rest of the acts of Jehoash that he did, and his might, and how he fought with Amaziah king of Judah, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel?",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And Jehoash slept with his fathers and was buried in Samaria with the kings of Israel, and Jeroboam his son reigned in his place.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9914Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9914Y\"></sup>Amaziah the son of Joash, king of Judah, lived fifteen years after the death of Jehoash son of Jehoahaz, king of Israel.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Now the rest of the deeds of Amaziah, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Judah?",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And they made a conspiracy against him in Jerusalem, and he fled to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9916Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9916Z\"></sup>Lachish. But they sent after him to Lachish and put him to death there.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And they brought him on horses; and he was buried in Jerusalem with his fathers in the city of David.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And all the people of Judah took Azariah, who was sixteen years old, and made him king instead of his father Amaziah.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>He built <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9919AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9919AA\"></sup>Elath and restored it to Judah, after the king slept with his fathers.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>In the fifteenth year of Amaziah the son of Joash, king of Judah, Jeroboam the son of Joash, king of Israel, began to reign in Samaria, and he reigned forty-one years.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And he did what was evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. He did not depart from all the sins of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9921AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9921AB\"></sup>which he made Israel to sin.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9922AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9922AC\"></sup>He restored the border of Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9922AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9922AD\"></sup>from Lebo-hamath as far as the Sea of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9922AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9922AE\"></sup>the Arabah, according to the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, which he spoke by his servant <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9922AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9922AF\"></sup>Jonah the son of Amittai, the prophet, who was from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9922AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9922AG\"></sup>Gath-hepher.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>For the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9923AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9923AH\"></sup>saw that the affliction of Israel was very bitter, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9923AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9923AI\"></sup>for there was none left, bond or free, and there was none to help Israel.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9924AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9924AJ\"></sup>But the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had not said that he would blot out the name of Israel from under heaven, so he saved them by the hand of Jeroboam the son of Joash.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Now the rest of the acts of Jeroboam and all that he did, and his might, how he fought, and how he restored <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9925AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9925AK\"></sup>Damascus and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9925AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9925AL\"></sup>Hamath to Judah in Israel, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel?",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>And Jeroboam slept with his fathers, the kings of Israel, and Zechariah his son reigned in his place."
		},
		"15": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">15 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9927A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9927A\"></sup>In the twenty-seventh year of Jeroboam king of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9927B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9927B\"></sup>Azariah the son of Amaziah, king of Judah, began to reign.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9928C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9928C\"></sup>sixteen years old when he began to reign, and he reigned fifty-two years in Jerusalem. His mother's name was Jecoliah of Jerusalem.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And he did what was right in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, according to all that his father Amaziah had done.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9930D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9930D\"></sup>Nevertheless, the high places were not taken away. The people still sacrificed and made offerings on the high places.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9931E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9931E\"></sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> touched the king, so that he was a leper to the day of his death, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9931F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9931F\"></sup>and he lived in a separate house. And Jotham the king's son was over the household, governing the people of the land.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Now the rest of the acts of Azariah, and all that he did, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Judah?",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And Azariah slept with his fathers, and they buried him with his fathers <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9933G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9933G\"></sup>in the city of David, and Jotham his son reigned in his place.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>In the thirty-eighth year of Azariah king of Judah, Zechariah the son of Jeroboam reigned over Israel in Samaria six months.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And he did what was evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, as his fathers had done. He did not depart from the sins of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9935H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9935H\"></sup>which he made Israel to sin.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Shallum the son of Jabesh conspired against him and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9936I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9936I\"></sup>struck him down at Ibleam and put him to death and reigned in his place.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Now the rest of the deeds of Zechariah, behold, they are written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>(This was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9938J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9938J\"></sup>the promise of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> that he gave to Jehu, “Your sons shall sit on the throne of Israel to the fourth generation.” And so it came to pass.)",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Shallum the son of Jabesh began to reign in the thirty-ninth year of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9939K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9939K\"></sup>Uzziah king of Judah, and he reigned one month in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9939L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9939L\"></sup>Samaria.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then Menahem the son of Gadi came up from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9940M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9940M\"></sup>Tirzah and came to Samaria, and he struck down Shallum the son of Jabesh in Samaria and put him to death and reigned in his place.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Now the rest of the deeds of Shallum, and the conspiracy that he made, behold, they are written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>At that time Menahem sacked Tiphsah and all who were in it and its territory from Tirzah on, because they did not open it to him. Therefore he sacked it, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9942N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9942N\"></sup>and he ripped open all the women in it who were pregnant.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>In the thirty-ninth year of Azariah king of Judah, Menahem the son of Gadi began to reign over Israel, and he reigned ten years in Samaria.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And he did what was evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. He did not depart all his days from all the sins of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, which he made Israel to sin.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9945O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9945O\"></sup>Pul the king of Assyria came against the land, and Menahem gave <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9945P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9945P\"></sup>Pul a thousand talents of silver, that he might help him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9945Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9945Q\"></sup>to confirm his hold on the royal power.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Menahem exacted the money from Israel, that is, from all the wealthy men, fifty shekels of silver from every man, to give to the king of Assyria. So the king of Assyria turned back and did not stay there in the land.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Now the rest of the deeds of Menahem and all that he did, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel?",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And Menahem slept with his fathers, and Pekahiah his son reigned in his place.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>In the fiftieth year of Azariah king of Judah, Pekahiah the son of Menahem began to reign over Israel in Samaria, and he reigned two years.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And he did what was evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. He did not turn away from the sins of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9950R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9950R\"></sup>which he made Israel to sin.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And Pekah the son of Remaliah, his captain, conspired against him with fifty men of the people of Gilead, and struck him down in Samaria, in the citadel of the king's house with Argob and Arieh; he put him to death and reigned in his place.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Now the rest of the deeds of Pekahiah and all that he did, behold, they are written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>In the fifty-second year of Azariah king of Judah, Pekah the son of Remaliah began to reign over Israel in Samaria, and he reigned twenty years.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>And he did what was evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. He did not depart from the sins of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9954S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9954S\"></sup>which he made Israel to sin.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>In the days of Pekah king of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9955T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9955T\"></sup>Tiglath-pileser king of Assyria came and captured <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9955U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9955U\"></sup>Ijon, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9955V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9955V\"></sup>Abel-beth-maacah, Janoah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9955W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9955W\"></sup>Kedesh, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9955X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9955X\"></sup>Hazor, Gilead, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9955Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9955Y\"></sup>Galilee, all the land of Naphtali, and he carried the people captive to Assyria.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Then Hoshea the son of Elah made a conspiracy against Pekah the son of Remaliah and struck him down and put him to death and reigned in his place, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9956Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9956Z\"></sup>in the twentieth year of Jotham the son of Uzziah.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Now the rest of the acts of Pekah and all that he did, behold, they are written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>In the second year of Pekah the son of Remaliah, king of Israel, Jotham the son of Uzziah, king of Judah, began to reign.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>He was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9959AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9959AA\"></sup>twenty-five years old when he began to reign, and he reigned sixteen years in Jerusalem. His mother's name was Jerusha the daughter of Zadok.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>And he did what was right in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9960AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9960AB\"></sup>according to all that his father Uzziah had done.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9961AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9961AC\"></sup>Nevertheless, the high places were not removed. The people still sacrificed and made offerings on the high places. He built <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9961AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9961AD\"></sup>the upper gate of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Now the rest of the acts of Jotham and all that he did, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Judah?",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>In those days the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> began to send <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9963AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9963AE\"></sup>Rezin the king of Syria and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9963AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9963AF\"></sup>Pekah the son of Remaliah against Judah.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Jotham slept with his fathers and was buried with his fathers in the city of David his father, and Ahaz his son reigned in his place."
		},
		"16": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">16 </span>In the seventeenth year of Pekah the son of Remaliah, Ahaz the son of Jotham, king of Judah, began to reign.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Ahaz was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9966A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9966A\"></sup>twenty years old when he began to reign, and he reigned sixteen years in Jerusalem. And he did not do what was right in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God, as his father David had done,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>but he walked in the way of the kings of Israel. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9967B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9967B\"></sup>He even burned his son as an offering, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9967C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9967C\"></sup>according to the despicable practices of the nations whom the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> drove out before the people of Israel.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9968D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9968D\"></sup>And he sacrificed and made offerings <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9968E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9968E\"></sup>on the high places and on the hills and under every green tree.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9969F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9969F\"></sup>Then Rezin king of Syria and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9969G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9969G\"></sup>Pekah the son of Remaliah, king of Israel, came up to wage war on Jerusalem, and they besieged Ahaz <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9969H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9969H\"></sup>but could not conquer him.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>At that time Rezin the king of Syria recovered <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9970I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9970I\"></sup>Elath for Syria and drove the men of Judah from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9970J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9970J\"></sup>Elath, and the Edomites came to Elath, where they dwell to this day.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9971K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9971K\"></sup>So Ahaz sent messengers to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9971L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9971L\"></sup>Tiglath-pileser king of Assyria, saying, “I am your servant and your son. Come up and rescue me from the hand of the king of Syria and from the hand of the king of Israel, who are attacking me.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Ahaz also <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9972M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9972M\"></sup>took the silver and gold that was found in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and in the treasures of the king's house and sent a present to the king of Assyria.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9973N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9973N\"></sup>And the king of Assyria listened to him. The king of Assyria marched up against Damascus <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9973O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9973O\"></sup>and took it, carrying its people captive to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9973P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9973P\"></sup>Kir, and he killed Rezin.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>When King Ahaz went to Damascus to meet <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9974Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9974Q\"></sup>Tiglath-pileser king of Assyria, he saw the altar that was at Damascus. And King Ahaz sent to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9974R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9974R\"></sup>Uriah the priest a model of the altar, and its pattern, exact in all its details.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And Uriah the priest built the altar; in accordance with all that King Ahaz had sent from Damascus, so Uriah the priest made it, before King Ahaz arrived from Damascus.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And when the king came from Damascus, the king viewed the altar. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9976S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9976S\"></sup>Then the king drew near to the altar and went up on it",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>and burned his burnt offering and his grain offering and poured his drink offering and threw the blood of his peace offerings on the altar.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9978T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9978T\"></sup>the bronze altar that was before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> he removed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9978U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9978U\"></sup>from the front of the house, from the place between <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9978V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9978V\"></sup>his altar and the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and put it on the north side of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9978W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9978W\"></sup>his altar.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And King Ahaz commanded Uriah the priest, saying, “On the great altar burn <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9979X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9979X\"></sup>the morning burnt offering and the evening grain offering and the king's burnt offering and his grain offering, with the burnt offering of all the people of the land, and their grain offering and their drink offering. And throw on it all the blood of the burnt offering and all the blood of the sacrifice, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9979Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9979Y\"></sup>the bronze altar shall be for me to inquire by.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Uriah the priest did all this, as King Ahaz commanded.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And King Ahaz cut off the frames of the stands and removed the basin from them, and he took down <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9981Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9981Z\"></sup>the sea from off the bronze oxen that were under it and put it on a stone pedestal.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And the covered way for the Sabbath that had been built inside the house and the outer entrance for the king he caused to go around the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, because of the king of Assyria.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Now the rest of the acts of Ahaz that he did, are they not written <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9983AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9983AA\"></sup>in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Judah?",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And Ahaz slept with his fathers and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9984AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9984AB\"></sup>was buried with his fathers in the city of David, and Hezekiah his son reigned in his place."
		},
		"17": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">17 </span>In the twelfth year of Ahaz king of Judah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9985A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9985A\"></sup>Hoshea the son of Elah began to reign in Samaria over Israel, and he reigned nine years.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And he did what was evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, yet not as the kings of Israel who were before him.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9987B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9987B\"></sup>Against him came up <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9987C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9987C\"></sup>Shalmaneser king of Assyria. And Hoshea became his vassal and paid him tribute.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But the king of Assyria found treachery in Hoshea, for he had sent messengers to So, king of Egypt, and offered no tribute to the king of Assyria, as he had done year by year. Therefore the king of Assyria shut him up and bound him in prison.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then the king of Assyria invaded all the land and came to Samaria, and for three years he besieged it.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>In the ninth year of Hoshea, the king of Assyria <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9990D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9990D\"></sup>captured Samaria, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9990E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9990E\"></sup>and he carried the Israelites away to Assyria <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9990F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9990F\"></sup>and placed them in Halah, and on the Habor, the river of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9990G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9990G\"></sup>Gozan, and in the cities of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9990H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9990H\"></sup>the Medes.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And this occurred because the people of Israel had sinned against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> their God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9991I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9991I\"></sup>who had brought them up out of the land of Egypt from under the hand of Pharaoh king of Egypt, and had feared other gods",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9992J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9992J\"></sup>and walked in the customs of the nations whom the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> drove out before the people of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9992K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9992K\"></sup>and in the customs that the kings of Israel had practiced.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And the people of Israel did secretly against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> their God things that were not right. They built for themselves high places in all their towns, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9993L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9993L\"></sup>from watchtower to fortified city.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>They set up for themselves <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9994M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9994M\"></sup>pillars and Asherim on every high hill and under every green tree,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>and there they made offerings on all the high places, as the nations did whom the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> carried away before them. And they did wicked things, provoking the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to anger,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>and they served idols, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9996N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9996N\"></sup>of which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had said to them, “You shall not do this.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Yet the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9997O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9997O\"></sup>warned Israel and Judah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9997P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9997P\"></sup>by every prophet <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9997Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9997Q\"></sup>and every seer, saying, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9997R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9997R\"></sup>“Turn from your evil ways and keep my commandments and my statutes, in accordance with all the Law that I commanded your fathers, and that I sent to you by my servants the prophets.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>But they would not listen, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9998S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9998S\"></sup>but were stubborn, as their fathers had been, who did not believe in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> their God.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>They despised his statutes <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9999T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9999T\"></sup>and his covenant that he made with their fathers and the warnings that he gave them. They went after <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9999U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9999U\"></sup>false idols <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9999V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9999V\"></sup>and became false, and they followed the nations that were around them, concerning whom the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9999W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9999W\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded them that they should not do like them.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And they abandoned all the commandments of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> their God, and made for themselves metal images of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10000X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10000X\"></sup>two calves; and they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10000Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10000Y\"></sup>made an Asherah and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10000Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10000Z\"></sup>worshiped all the host of heaven and served <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10000AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10000AA\"></sup>Baal.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10001AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10001AB\"></sup>And they burned their sons and their daughters as offerings and used <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10001AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10001AC\"></sup>divination and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10001AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10001AD\"></sup>omens and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10001AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10001AE\"></sup>sold themselves to do evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, provoking him to anger.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Therefore the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was very angry with Israel and removed them out of his sight. None was left but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10002AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10002AF\"></sup>the tribe of Judah only.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10003AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10003AG\"></sup>Judah also did not keep the commandments of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> their God, but walked in the customs that Israel had introduced.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> rejected all the descendants of Israel and afflicted them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10004AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10004AH\"></sup>and gave them into the hand of plunderers, until he had cast them out of his sight.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10005AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10005AI\"></sup>When he had torn Israel from the house of David, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10005AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10005AJ\"></sup>they made Jeroboam the son of Nebat king. And Jeroboam drove Israel from following the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10005AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10005AK\"></sup>and made them commit great sin.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The people of Israel walked in all the sins that Jeroboam did. They did not depart from them,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>until the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> removed Israel out of his sight, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10007AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10007AL\"></sup>as he had spoken by all his servants the prophets. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10007AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10007AM\"></sup>So Israel was exiled from their own land to Assyria until this day.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10008AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10008AN\"></sup>And the king of Assyria brought people from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10008AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10008AO\"></sup>Babylon, Cuthah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10008AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10008AP\"></sup>Avva, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10008AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10008AQ\"></sup>Hamath, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10008AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10008AR\"></sup>Sepharvaim, and placed them in the cities of Samaria instead of the people of Israel. And they took possession of Samaria and lived in its cities.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And at the beginning of their dwelling there, they did not fear the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. Therefore the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> sent lions among them, which killed some of them.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>So the king of Assyria was told, “The nations that you have carried away and placed in the cities of Samaria do not know the law of the god of the land. Therefore he has sent lions among them, and behold, they are killing them, because they do not know the law of the god of the land.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Then the king of Assyria commanded, “Send there one of the priests whom you carried away from there, and let him go and dwell there and teach them the law of the god of the land.”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>So one of the priests whom they had carried away from Samaria came and lived in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10012AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10012AS\"></sup>Bethel and taught them how they should fear the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>But every nation still made gods of its own and put them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10013AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10013AT\"></sup>in the shrines of the high places that the Samaritans had made, every nation in the cities in which they lived.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>The men of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10014AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10014AU\"></sup>Babylon made Succoth-benoth, the men of Cuth made Nergal, the men of Hamath made Ashima,",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>and the Avvites made Nibhaz and Tartak; and the Sepharvites <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10015AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10015AV\"></sup>burned their children in the fire to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10015AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10015AW\"></sup>Adrammelech and Anammelech, the gods of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10015AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10015AX\"></sup>Sepharvaim.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10016AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10016AY\"></sup>They also feared the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10016AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10016AZ\"></sup>and appointed from among themselves all sorts of people as priests of the high places, who sacrificed for them in the shrines of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10016BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10016BA\"></sup>the high places.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>So they feared the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> but also served their own gods, after the manner of the nations from among whom they had been carried away.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>To this day they do according to the former manner. They do not fear the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and they do not follow the statutes or the rules or the law or the commandment that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded the children of Jacob, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10018BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10018BB\"></sup>whom he named Israel.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> made a covenant with them and commanded them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10019BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10019BC\"></sup>“You shall not fear other gods <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10019BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10019BD\"></sup>or bow yourselves to them or serve them or sacrifice to them,",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10020BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10020BE\"></sup>you shall fear the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10020BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10020BF\"></sup>who brought you out of the land of Egypt with great power and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10020BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10020BG\"></sup>with an outstretched arm. You shall bow yourselves to him, and to him you shall sacrifice.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>And the statutes and the rules and the law and the commandment that he wrote for you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10021BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10021BH\"></sup>you shall always be careful to do. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10021BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10021BI\"></sup>You shall not fear other gods,",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10022BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10022BJ\"></sup>you shall not forget the covenant that I have made with you. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10022BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10022BK\"></sup>You shall not fear other gods,",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10023BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10023BL\"></sup>you shall fear the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, and he will deliver you out of the hand of all your enemies.”",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>However, they would not listen, but they did according to their former manner.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10025BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10025BM\"></sup>So these nations feared the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and also served their carved images. Their children did likewise, and their children's children—as their fathers did, so they do to this day."
		},
		"18": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">18 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10026A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10026A\"></sup>In the third year of Hoshea son of Elah, king of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10026B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10026B\"></sup>Hezekiah the son of Ahaz, king of Judah, began to reign.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10027C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10027C\"></sup>twenty-five years old when he began to reign, and he reigned twenty-nine years in Jerusalem. His mother's name was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10027D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10027D\"></sup>Abi the daughter of Zechariah.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10028E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10028E\"></sup>And he did what was right in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, according to all that David his father had done.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10029F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10029F\"></sup>He removed the high places and broke the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10029G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10029G\"></sup>pillars and cut down <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10029H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10029H\"></sup>the Asherah. And he broke in pieces <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10029I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10029I\"></sup>the bronze serpent that Moses had made, for until those days the people of Israel had made offerings to it (it was called Nehushtan).",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10030J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10030J\"></sup>He trusted in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10030K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10030K\"></sup>so that there was none like him among all the kings of Judah after him, nor among those who were before him.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10031L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10031L\"></sup>For he held fast to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. He did not depart from following him, but kept the commandments that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded Moses.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10032M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10032M\"></sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was with him; wherever he went out, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10032N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10032N\"></sup>he prospered. He rebelled against the king of Assyria and would not serve him.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10033O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10033O\"></sup>He struck down the Philistines as far as Gaza and its territory, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10033P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10033P\"></sup>from watchtower to fortified city.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>In the fourth year of King Hezekiah, which was the seventh year of Hoshea son of Elah, king of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10034Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10034Q\"></sup>Shalmaneser king of Assyria came up against Samaria and besieged it,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>and at the end of three years he took it. In the sixth year of Hezekiah, which was the ninth year of Hoshea king of Israel, Samaria was taken.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The king of Assyria carried the Israelites away to Assyria and put them in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10036R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10036R\"></sup>Halah, and on the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10036S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10036S\"></sup>Habor, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10036T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10036T\"></sup>the river of Gozan, and in the cities of the Medes,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>because they did not obey the voice of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> their God but transgressed his covenant, even all that Moses the servant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded. They neither listened nor obeyed.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10038U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10038U\"></sup>In the fourteenth year of King Hezekiah, Sennacherib king of Assyria came up against all the fortified cities of Judah and took them.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And Hezekiah king of Judah sent to the king of Assyria at Lachish, saying, “I have done wrong; withdraw from me. Whatever you impose on me I will bear.” <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10039V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10039V\"></sup>And the king of Assyria required of Hezekiah king of Judah three hundred talents of silver and thirty talents of gold.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And Hezekiah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10040W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10040W\"></sup>gave him all the silver that was found in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and in the treasuries of the king's house.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>At that time Hezekiah stripped the gold from the doors of the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and from the doorposts that Hezekiah king of Judah had overlaid and gave it to the king of Assyria.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And the king of Assyria sent the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10042X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10042X\"></sup>Tartan, the Rab-saris, and the Rabshakeh with a great army from Lachish to King Hezekiah at Jerusalem. And they went up and came to Jerusalem. When they arrived, they came and stood by <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10042Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10042Y\"></sup>the conduit of the upper pool, which is on the highway to the Washer's Field.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And when they called for the king, there came out to them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10043Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10043Z\"></sup>Eliakim the son of Hilkiah, who was over the household, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10043AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10043AA\"></sup>Shebnah the secretary, and Joah the son of Asaph, the recorder.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And the Rabshakeh said to them, “Say to Hezekiah, ‘Thus says the great king, the king of Assyria: On what do you rest this trust of yours?",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Do you think that mere words are strategy and power for war? In whom do you now trust, that you have rebelled against me?",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Behold, you are trusting now in Egypt, that broken reed of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10046AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10046AB\"></sup>a staff, which will pierce the hand of any man who leans on it. Such is Pharaoh king of Egypt to all who trust in him.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>But if you say to me, “We trust in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God,” is it not he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10047AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10047AC\"></sup>whose high places and altars Hezekiah has removed, saying to Judah and to Jerusalem, “You shall worship before this altar in Jerusalem”?",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Come now, make a wager with my master the king of Assyria: I will give you two thousand horses, if you are able on your part to set riders on them.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>How then can you repulse a single captain among the least of my master's servants, when you trust in Egypt for chariots and for horsemen?",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Moreover, is it without the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> that I have come up against this place to destroy it? The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to me, “Go up against this land and destroy it.”’”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10051AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10051AD\"></sup>Eliakim the son of Hilkiah, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10051AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10051AE\"></sup>Shebnah, and Joah, said to the Rabshakeh, “Please speak to your servants in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10051AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10051AF\"></sup>Aramaic, for we understand it. Do not speak to us in the language of Judah within the hearing of the people who are on the wall.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>But the Rabshakeh said to them, “Has my master sent me to speak these words to your master and to you, and not to the men sitting on the wall, who are doomed with you to eat their own dung and to drink their own urine?”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Then the Rabshakeh stood and called out in a loud voice in the language of Judah: “Hear the word of the great king, the king of Assyria!",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Thus says the king: ‘Do not let Hezekiah deceive you, for he will not be able to deliver you out of my hand.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Do not let Hezekiah make you trust in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> by saying, The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will surely deliver us, and this city will not be given into the hand of the king of Assyria.’",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Do not listen to Hezekiah, for thus says the king of Assyria: ‘Make your peace with me and come out to me. Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10056AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10056AG\"></sup>each one of you will eat of his own vine, and each one of his own fig tree, and each one of you will drink the water of his own cistern,",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>until I come and take you away to a land like your own land, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10057AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10057AH\"></sup>a land of grain and wine, a land of bread and vineyards, a land of olive trees and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10057AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10057AI\"></sup>honey, that you may live, and not die. And do not listen to Hezekiah when he misleads you by saying, “The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will deliver us.”",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10058AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10058AJ\"></sup>Has any of the gods of the nations ever delivered his land out of the hand of the king of Assyria?",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10059AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10059AK\"></sup>Where are the gods of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10059AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10059AL\"></sup>Hamath and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10059AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10059AM\"></sup>Arpad? Where are the gods of Sepharvaim, Hena, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10059AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10059AN\"></sup>Ivvah? Have they delivered Samaria out of my hand?",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Who among all the gods of the lands have delivered their lands out of my hand, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10060AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10060AO\"></sup>that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> should deliver Jerusalem out of my hand?’”",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>But the people were silent and answered him not a word, for the king's command was, “Do not answer him.”",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10062AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10062AP\"></sup>Eliakim the son of Hilkiah, who was over the household, and Shebna the secretary, and Joah the son of Asaph, the recorder, came to Hezekiah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10062AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10062AQ\"></sup>with their clothes torn and told him the words of the Rabshakeh."
		},
		"19": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">19 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10063A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10063A\"></sup>As soon as King Hezekiah heard it, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10063B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10063B\"></sup>he tore his clothes and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10063C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10063C\"></sup>covered himself with sackcloth and went into the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And he sent Eliakim, who was over the household, and Shebna the secretary, and the senior priests, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10064D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10064D\"></sup>covered with sackcloth, to the prophet Isaiah the son of Amoz.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>They said to him, “Thus says Hezekiah, This day is a day of distress, of rebuke, and of disgrace; children have come to the point of birth, and there is no strength to bring them forth.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10066E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10066E\"></sup>It may be that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God heard all the words of the Rabshakeh, whom his master the king of Assyria has sent <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10066F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10066F\"></sup>to mock the living God, and will rebuke the words that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has heard; therefore lift up your prayer for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10066G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10066G\"></sup>the remnant that is left.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>When the servants of King Hezekiah came to Isaiah,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Isaiah said to them, “Say to your master, ‘Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>: Do not be afraid because of the words that you have heard, with which <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10068H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10068H\"></sup>the servants of the king of Assyria have <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10068I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10068I\"></sup>reviled me.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Behold, I will put a spirit in him, so that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10069J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10069J\"></sup>he shall hear a rumor and return to his own land, and I will make him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10069K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10069K\"></sup>fall by the sword in his own land.’”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The Rabshakeh returned, and found the king of Assyria fighting against <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10070L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10070L\"></sup>Libnah, for he heard that the king had left <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10070M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10070M\"></sup>Lachish.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10071N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10071N\"></sup>Now the king heard concerning Tirhakah king of Cush, “Behold, he has set out to fight against you.” So he sent messengers again to Hezekiah, saying,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“Thus shall you speak to Hezekiah king of Judah: ‘Do not let your God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10072O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10072O\"></sup>in whom you trust deceive you by promising that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10072P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10072P\"></sup>Jerusalem will not be given into the hand of the king of Assyria.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Behold, you have heard what the kings of Assyria have done to all lands, devoting them to destruction. And shall you be delivered?",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10074Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10074Q\"></sup>Have the gods of the nations delivered them, the nations that my fathers destroyed, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10074R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10074R\"></sup>Gozan, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10074S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10074S\"></sup>Haran, Rezeph, and the people of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10074T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10074T\"></sup>Eden who were in Telassar?",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10075U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10075U\"></sup>Where is the king of Hamath, the king of Arpad, the king of the city of Sepharvaim, the king of Hena, or the king of Ivvah?’”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Hezekiah received <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10076V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10076V\"></sup>the letter from the hand of the messengers and read it; and Hezekiah went up to the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and spread it before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And Hezekiah prayed before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and said: “O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10077W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10077W\"></sup>enthroned above the cherubim, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10077X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10077X\"></sup>you are the God, you alone, of all the kingdoms of the earth; you have made heaven and earth.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10078Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10078Y\"></sup>Incline your ear, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and hear; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10078Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10078Z\"></sup>open your eyes, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and see; and hear the words of Sennacherib, which he has sent <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10078AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10078AA\"></sup>to mock the living God.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Truly, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the kings of Assyria have laid waste the nations and their lands",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>and have cast their gods into the fire, for they were not gods, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10080AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10080AB\"></sup>but the work of men's hands, wood and stone. Therefore they were destroyed.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>So now, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God, save us, please, from his hand, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10081AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10081AC\"></sup>that all the kingdoms of the earth may know that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10081AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10081AD\"></sup>you, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, are God alone.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then Isaiah the son of Amoz sent to Hezekiah, saying, “Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel: Your prayer to me about Sennacherib king of Assyria <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10082AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10082AE\"></sup>I have heard.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>This is the word that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has spoken concerning him:“She despises you, she scorns you—<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10083AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10083AF\"></sup>the virgin daughter of Zion;she <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10083AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10083AG\"></sup>wags her head behind you—the daughter of Jerusalem.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“Whom have you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10084AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10084AH\"></sup>mocked and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10084AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10084AI\"></sup>reviled?Against whom have you raised your voiceand lifted your eyes to the heights?Against <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10084AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10084AJ\"></sup>the Holy One of Israel!",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10085AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10085AK\"></sup>By your messengers you have mocked the Lord,and you have said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10085AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10085AL\"></sup>‘With my many chariotsI have gone up the heights of the mountains,to the far recesses of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10085AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10085AM\"></sup>Lebanon;I felled its tallest cedars,its choicest cypresses;I entered its farthest lodging place,its most <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10085AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10085AN\"></sup>fruitful forest.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>I dug wellsand drank foreign waters,and I dried up with the sole of my footall the streams <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10086AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10086AO\"></sup>of Egypt.’",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>“Have you not heardthat <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10087AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10087AP\"></sup>I determined it long ago?I planned from days of oldwhat <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10087AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10087AQ\"></sup>now I bring to pass,that you should turn fortified citiesinto heaps of ruins,",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>while their inhabitants, shorn of strength,are dismayed and confounded,and have become <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10088AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10088AR\"></sup>like plants of the fieldand like tender grass,like grass on the housetops,blighted before it is grown.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>“But I know your sitting down<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10089AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10089AS\"></sup>and your going out and coming in,and your raging against me.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Because you have raged against meand your complacency has come into my ears,I will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10090AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10090AT\"></sup>put my hook in your noseand my bit in your mouth,and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10090AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10090AU\"></sup>I will turn you back on the wayby which you came.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>“And this shall be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10091AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10091AV\"></sup>the sign for you: this year eat what grows of itself, and in the second year what springs of the same. Then in the third year sow and reap and plant vineyards, and eat their fruit.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10092AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10092AW\"></sup>And the surviving remnant of the house of Judah shall again take root downward and bear fruit upward.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>For out of Jerusalem shall go a remnant, and out of Mount Zion <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10093AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10093AX\"></sup>a band of survivors. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10093AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10093AY\"></sup>The zeal of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will do this.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>“Therefore thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> concerning the king of Assyria: He shall not come into this city or shoot an arrow there, or come before it with a shield or <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10094AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10094AZ\"></sup>cast up a siege mound against it.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10095BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10095BA\"></sup>By the way that he came, by the same he shall return, and he shall not come into this city, declares the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10096BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10096BB\"></sup>For I will defend this city to save it, for my own sake <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10096BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10096BC\"></sup>and for the sake of my servant David.”",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>And that night <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10097BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10097BD\"></sup>the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> went out and struck down 185,000 in the camp of the Assyrians. And when people arose early in the morning, behold, these were all dead bodies.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Then Sennacherib king of Assyria departed and went home and lived at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10098BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10098BE\"></sup>Nineveh.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>And as he was worshiping in the house of Nisroch his god, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10099BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10099BF\"></sup>Adrammelech and Sharezer, his sons, struck him down with the sword and escaped into the land of Ararat. And Esarhaddon his son reigned in his place."
		},
		"20": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">20 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10100A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10100A\"></sup>In those days <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10100B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10100B\"></sup>Hezekiah became sick and was at the point of death. And Isaiah the prophet the son of Amoz came to him and said to him, “Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10100C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10100C\"></sup>‘Set your house in order, for you shall die; you shall not recover.’”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Then Hezekiah turned his face to the wall and prayed to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, saying,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>“Now, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10102D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10102D\"></sup>please remember how I have walked before you in faithfulness and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10102E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10102E\"></sup>with a whole heart, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10102F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10102F\"></sup>and have done what is good in your sight.” <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10102G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10102G\"></sup>And Hezekiah wept bitterly.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And before Isaiah had gone out of the middle court, the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came to him:",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>“Turn back, and say to Hezekiah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10104H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10104H\"></sup>the leader of my people, Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of David your father: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10104I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10104I\"></sup>I have heard your prayer; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10104J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10104J\"></sup>I have seen your tears. Behold, I will heal you. On the third day you shall go up to the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>and I will add fifteen years to your life. I will deliver you and this city out of the hand of the king of Assyria, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10105K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10105K\"></sup>and I will defend this city for my own sake and for my servant David's sake.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And Isaiah said, “Bring a cake of figs. And let them take and lay it on the boil, that he may recover.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And Hezekiah said to Isaiah, “What shall be the sign that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will heal me, and that I shall go up to the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> on the third day?”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And Isaiah said, “This shall be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10108L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10108L\"></sup>the sign to you from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will do the thing that he has promised: shall the shadow go forward ten steps, or go back ten steps?”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And Hezekiah answered, “It is an easy thing for the shadow <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10109M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10109M\"></sup>to lengthen ten steps. Rather let the shadow go back ten steps.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And Isaiah the prophet called to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10110N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10110N\"></sup>and he brought the shadow back ten steps, by which it had gone down on the steps of Ahaz.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10111O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10111O\"></sup>At that time <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10111P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10111P\"></sup>Merodach-baladan the son of Baladan, king of Babylon, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10111Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10111Q\"></sup>sent envoys with letters and a present to Hezekiah, for he heard that Hezekiah had been sick.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And Hezekiah welcomed them, and he showed them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10112R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10112R\"></sup>all his treasure house, the silver, the gold, the spices, the precious oil, his armory, all that was found in his storehouses. There was nothing in his house or in all his realm that Hezekiah did not show them.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then Isaiah the prophet came to King Hezekiah, and said to him, “What did these men say? And from where did they come to you?” And Hezekiah said, “They have come from a far country, from Babylon.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>He said, “What have they seen in your house?” And Hezekiah answered, “They have seen all that is in my house; there is nothing in my storehouses that I did not show them.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then Isaiah said to Hezekiah, “Hear the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>:",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Behold, the days are coming, when <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10116S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10116S\"></sup>all that is in your house, and that which your fathers have stored up till this day, shall be carried to Babylon. Nothing shall be left, says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10117T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10117T\"></sup>And some of your own sons, who will come from you, whom you will father, shall be taken away, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10117U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10117U\"></sup>and they shall be eunuchs in the palace of the king of Babylon.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Then Hezekiah said to Isaiah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10118V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10118V\"></sup>“The word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> that you have spoken is good.” For he thought, “Why not, if there will be peace and security in my days?”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10119W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10119W\"></sup>The rest of the deeds of Hezekiah and all his might and how he made <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10119X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10119X\"></sup>the pool and the conduit <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10119Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10119Y\"></sup>and brought water into the city, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Judah?",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10120Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10120Z\"></sup>And Hezekiah slept with his fathers, and Manasseh his son reigned in his place."
		},
		"21": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">21 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10121A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10121A\"></sup>Manasseh was twelve years old when he began to reign, and he reigned fifty-five years in Jerusalem. His mother's name was Hephzibah.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And he did what was evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10122B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10122B\"></sup>according to the despicable practices of the nations whom the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> drove out before the people of Israel.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>For he rebuilt the high places <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10123C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10123C\"></sup>that Hezekiah his father had destroyed, and he erected altars for Baal and made <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10123D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10123D\"></sup>an Asherah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10123E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10123E\"></sup>as Ahab king of Israel had done, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10123F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10123F\"></sup>and worshiped all the host of heaven and served them.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10124G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10124G\"></sup>And he built altars in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, of which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10124H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10124H\"></sup>“In Jerusalem will I put my name.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And he built altars <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10125I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10125I\"></sup>for all the host of heaven in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10125J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10125J\"></sup>the two courts of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10126K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10126K\"></sup>And he burned his son as an offering and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10126L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10126L\"></sup>used fortune-telling and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10126M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10126M\"></sup>omens and dealt <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10126N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10126N\"></sup>with mediums and with necromancers. He did much evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, provoking him to anger.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And the carved image of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10127O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10127O\"></sup>Asherah that he had made he set in the house of which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to David and to Solomon his son, “In this house, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10127P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10127P\"></sup>and in Jerusalem, which I have chosen out of all the tribes of Israel, I will put my name forever.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10128Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10128Q\"></sup>And I will not cause the feet of Israel to wander anymore out of the land that I gave to their fathers, if only they will be careful to do according to all that I have commanded them, and according to all the Law that my servant Moses commanded them.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But they did not listen, and Manasseh led them astray to do more evil than the nations had done whom the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> destroyed before the people of Israel.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said by his servants the prophets,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10131R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10131R\"></sup>“Because Manasseh king of Judah has committed these abominations and has done things <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10131S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10131S\"></sup>more evil than all that the Amorites did, who were before him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10131T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10131T\"></sup>and has made Judah also to sin <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10131U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10131U\"></sup>with his idols,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>therefore thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel: Behold, I am bringing upon Jerusalem and Judah such disaster that the ears of everyone who hears of it <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10132V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10132V\"></sup>will tingle.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10133W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10133W\"></sup>And I will stretch over Jerusalem the measuring line of Samaria, and the plumb line of the house of Ahab, and I will wipe Jerusalem as one wipes a dish, wiping it and turning it upside down.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And I will forsake the remnant of my heritage and give them into the hand of their enemies, and they shall become a prey and a spoil to all their enemies,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>because they have done what is evil in my sight and have provoked me to anger, since the day their fathers came out of Egypt, even to this day.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10136X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10136X\"></sup>Moreover, Manasseh shed very much innocent blood, till he had filled Jerusalem from one end to another, besides the sin <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10136Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10136Y\"></sup>that he made Judah to sin so that they did what was evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10137Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10137Z\"></sup>Now the rest of the acts of Manasseh and all that he did, and the sin that he committed, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Judah?",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10138AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10138AA\"></sup>And Manasseh slept with his fathers and was buried in the garden of his house, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10138AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10138AB\"></sup>in the garden of Uzza, and Amon his son reigned in his place.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Amon was twenty-two years old when he began to reign, and he reigned two years in Jerusalem. His mother's name was Meshullemeth the daughter of Haruz of Jotbah.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And he did what was evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10140AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10140AC\"></sup>as Manasseh his father had done.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>He walked in all the way in which his father walked and served <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10141AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10141AD\"></sup>the idols that his father served and worshiped them.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10142AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10142AE\"></sup>He abandoned the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of his fathers, and did not walk in the way of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And the servants of Amon conspired against him and put the king to death in his house.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>But the people of the land struck down all those who had conspired against King Amon, and the people of the land made Josiah his son king in his place.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Now the rest of the acts of Amon that he did, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Judah?",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And he was buried in his tomb <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10146AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10146AF\"></sup>in the garden of Uzza, and Josiah his son reigned in his place."
		},
		"22": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">22 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10147A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10147A\"></sup>Josiah was eight years old when he began to reign, and he reigned thirty-one years in Jerusalem. His mother's name was Jedidah the daughter of Adaiah of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10147B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10147B\"></sup>Bozkath.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And he did what was right in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and walked in all the way of David his father, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10148C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10148C\"></sup>and he did not turn aside to the right or to the left.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>In the eighteenth year of King Josiah, the king sent Shaphan the son of Azaliah, son of Meshullam, the secretary, to the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, saying,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“Go up to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10150D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10150D\"></sup>Hilkiah the high priest, that he may count the money <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10150E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10150E\"></sup>that has been brought into the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, which <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10150F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10150F\"></sup>the keepers of the threshold have collected from the people.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10151G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10151G\"></sup>And let it be given into the hand of the workmen who have the oversight of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and let them give it to the workmen who are at the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, repairing the house",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>(that is, to the carpenters, and to the builders, and to the masons), and let them use it for buying timber and quarried stone to repair the house.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10153H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10153H\"></sup>no accounting shall be asked from them for the money that is delivered into their hand, for they deal honestly.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And Hilkiah the high priest said to Shaphan the secretary, “I have found <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10154I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10154I\"></sup>the Book of the Law in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.” And Hilkiah gave the book to Shaphan, and he read it.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And Shaphan the secretary came to the king, and reported to the king, “Your servants have emptied out the money that was found in the house and have delivered it into the hand of the workmen who have the oversight of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then Shaphan the secretary told the king, “Hilkiah the priest has given me a book.” And Shaphan read it before the king.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>When the king heard the words of the Book of the Law, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10157J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10157J\"></sup>he tore his clothes.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And the king commanded Hilkiah the priest, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10158K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10158K\"></sup>Ahikam the son of Shaphan, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10158L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10158L\"></sup>Achbor the son of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10158M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10158M\"></sup>Micaiah, and Shaphan the secretary, and Asaiah the king's servant, saying,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“Go, inquire of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for me, and for the people, and for all Judah, concerning the words of this book that has been found. For great is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10159N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10159N\"></sup>the wrath of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> that is kindled against us, because our fathers have not obeyed the words of this book, to do according to all that is written concerning us.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>So Hilkiah the priest, and Ahikam, and Achbor, and Shaphan, and Asaiah went to Huldah the prophetess, the wife of Shallum the son of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10160O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10160O\"></sup>Tikvah, son of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10160P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10160P\"></sup>Harhas, keeper of the wardrobe (now she lived in Jerusalem in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10160Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10160Q\"></sup>the Second Quarter), and they talked with her.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And she said to them, “Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel: ‘Tell the man who sent you to me,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, Behold, I will bring disaster upon this place and upon its inhabitants, all the words of the book that the king of Judah has read.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10163R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10163R\"></sup>Because they have forsaken me and have made offerings to other gods, that they might provoke me to anger with all the work of their hands, therefore <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10163S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10163S\"></sup>my wrath will be kindled against this place, and it will not be quenched.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>But to the king of Judah, who sent you to inquire of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, thus shall you say to him, Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel: Regarding the words that you have heard,",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10165T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10165T\"></sup>because your heart was penitent, and you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10165U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10165U\"></sup>humbled yourself before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, when you heard how I spoke against this place and against its inhabitants, that they should become <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10165V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10165V\"></sup>a desolation and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10165W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10165W\"></sup>a curse, and you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10165X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10165X\"></sup>have torn your clothes and wept before me, I also have heard you, declares the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Therefore, behold, I will gather you to your fathers, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10166Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10166Y\"></sup>you shall be gathered to your grave in peace, and your eyes shall not see all the disaster that I will bring upon this place.’” And they brought back word to the king."
		},
		"23": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">23 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10167A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10167A\"></sup>Then the king sent, and all the elders of Judah and Jerusalem were gathered to him.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And the king went up to the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and with him all the men of Judah and all the inhabitants of Jerusalem and the priests and the prophets, all the people, both small and great. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10168B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10168B\"></sup>he read in their hearing all the words of the Book of the Covenant <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10168C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10168C\"></sup>that had been found in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And the king stood <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10169D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10169D\"></sup>by the pillar and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10169E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10169E\"></sup>made a covenant before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10169F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10169F\"></sup>to walk after the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and to keep his commandments and his testimonies and his statutes with all his heart and all his soul, to perform the words of this covenant that were written in this book. And all the people joined in the covenant.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And the king commanded Hilkiah the high priest and the priests <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10170G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10170G\"></sup>of the second order and the keepers of the threshold to bring out of the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> all the vessels made for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10170H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10170H\"></sup>Baal, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10170I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10170I\"></sup>Asherah, and for all the host of heaven. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10170J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10170J\"></sup>He burned them outside Jerusalem in the fields of the Kidron and carried their ashes to Bethel.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And he deposed the priests whom the kings of Judah had ordained to make offerings in the high places at the cities of Judah and around Jerusalem; those also who burned incense to Baal, to the sun and the moon and the constellations <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10171K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10171K\"></sup>and all the host of the heavens.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And he brought out <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10172L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10172L\"></sup>the Asherah from the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, outside Jerusalem, to the brook Kidron, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10172M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10172M\"></sup>and burned it at the brook Kidron <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10172N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10172N\"></sup>and beat it to dust and cast the dust of it upon the graves <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10172O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10172O\"></sup>of the common people.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And he broke down the houses of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10173P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10173P\"></sup>the male cult prostitutes who were in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10173Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10173Q\"></sup>where the women wove hangings for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10173R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10173R\"></sup>the Asherah.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And he brought all the priests out of the cities of Judah, and defiled the high places where the priests had made offerings, from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10174S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10174S\"></sup>Geba to Beersheba. And he broke down the high places of the gates that were at the entrance of the gate of Joshua the governor of the city, which were on one's left at the gate of the city.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10175T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10175T\"></sup>However, the priests of the high places did not come up to the altar of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in Jerusalem, but they ate unleavened bread among their brothers.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And he defiled <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10176U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10176U\"></sup>Topheth, which is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10176V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10176V\"></sup>in the Valley of the Son of Hinnom, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10176W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10176W\"></sup>that no one might burn his son or his daughter as an offering to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10176X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10176X\"></sup>Molech.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And he removed the horses that the kings of Judah had dedicated to the sun, at the entrance to the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, by the chamber of Nathan-melech the chamberlain, which was in the precincts. And he burned the chariots of the sun with fire.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And the altars <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10178Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10178Y\"></sup>on the roof of the upper chamber of Ahaz, which the kings of Judah had made, and the altars <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10178Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10178Z\"></sup>that Manasseh had made in the two courts of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, he pulled down and broke in pieces and cast the dust of them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10178AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10178AA\"></sup>into the brook Kidron.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And the king defiled the high places that were east of Jerusalem, to the south of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10179AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10179AB\"></sup>the mount of corruption, which Solomon the king of Israel had built for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10179AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10179AC\"></sup>Ashtoreth the abomination of the Sidonians, and for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10179AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10179AD\"></sup>Chemosh the abomination of Moab, and for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10179AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10179AE\"></sup>Milcom the abomination of the Ammonites.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And he broke in pieces the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10180AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10180AF\"></sup>pillars and cut down the Asherim and filled their places with the bones of men.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Moreover, the altar at Bethel, the high place erected <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10181AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10181AG\"></sup>by Jeroboam the son of Nebat, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10181AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10181AH\"></sup>who made Israel to sin, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10181AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10181AI\"></sup>that altar with the high place he pulled down and burned, reducing it to dust. He also burned the Asherah.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And as Josiah turned, he saw the tombs there on the mount. And he sent and took the bones out of the tombs and burned them on the altar and defiled it, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10182AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10182AJ\"></sup>according to the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> that the man of God proclaimed, who had predicted these things.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then he said, “What is that monument that I see?” And the men of the city told him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10183AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10183AK\"></sup>“It is the tomb of the man of God who came from Judah and predicted these things that you have done against the altar at Bethel.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And he said, “Let him be; let no man move his bones.” So they let his bones alone, with the bones <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10184AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10184AL\"></sup>of the prophet who came out of Samaria.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And Josiah removed all the shrines also of the high places that were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10185AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10185AM\"></sup>in the cities of Samaria, which kings of Israel had made, provoking the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to anger. He did to them according to all that he had done at Bethel.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10186AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10186AN\"></sup>he sacrificed all the priests of the high places who were there, on the altars, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10186AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10186AO\"></sup>and burned human bones on them. Then he returned to Jerusalem.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And the king commanded all the people, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10187AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10187AP\"></sup>“Keep the Passover to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10187AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10187AQ\"></sup>as it is written in this Book of the Covenant.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10188AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10188AR\"></sup>For no such Passover had been kept since the days of the judges who judged Israel, or during all the days of the kings of Israel or of the kings of Judah.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>But in the eighteenth year of King Josiah this Passover was kept to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in Jerusalem.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Moreover, Josiah put away <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10190AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10190AS\"></sup>the mediums and the necromancers and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10190AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10190AT\"></sup>the household gods and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10190AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10190AU\"></sup>the idols and all the abominations that were seen in the land of Judah and in Jerusalem, that he might establish <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10190AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10190AV\"></sup>the words of the law that were written in the book <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10190AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10190AW\"></sup>that Hilkiah the priest found in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10191AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10191AX\"></sup>Before him there was no king like him, who turned to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> with all his heart and with all his soul and with all his might, according to all the Law of Moses, nor did any like him arise after him.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Still the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> did not turn from the burning of his great wrath, by which his anger was kindled against Judah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10192AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10192AY\"></sup>because of all the provocations with which Manasseh had provoked him.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said, “I will remove Judah also out of my sight, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10193AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10193AZ\"></sup>as I have removed Israel, and I will cast off this city that I have chosen, Jerusalem, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10193BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10193BA\"></sup>and the house of which I said, My name shall be there.”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Now the rest of the acts of Josiah and all that he did, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Judah?",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10195BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10195BB\"></sup>In his days <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10195BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10195BC\"></sup>Pharaoh Neco king of Egypt went up to the king of Assyria to the river Euphrates. King Josiah went to meet him, and Pharaoh Neco killed him at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10195BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10195BD\"></sup>Megiddo, as soon as he saw him.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10196BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10196BE\"></sup>And his servants carried him dead in a chariot from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10196BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10196BF\"></sup>Megiddo and brought him to Jerusalem and buried him in his own tomb. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10196BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10196BG\"></sup>And the people of the land took Jehoahaz the son of Josiah, and anointed him, and made him king in his father's place.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10197BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10197BH\"></sup>Jehoahaz was twenty-three years old when he began to reign, and he reigned three months in Jerusalem. His mother's name was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10197BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10197BI\"></sup>Hamutal the daughter of Jeremiah of Libnah.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>And he did what was evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10198BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10198BJ\"></sup>according to all that his fathers had done.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10199BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10199BK\"></sup>Pharaoh Neco put him in bonds at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10199BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10199BL\"></sup>Riblah in the land of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10199BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10199BM\"></sup>Hamath, that he might not reign in Jerusalem, and laid on the land a tribute of a hundred talents of silver and a talent of gold.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10200BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10200BN\"></sup>Pharaoh Neco made Eliakim the son of Josiah king in the place of Josiah his father, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10200BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10200BO\"></sup>changed his name to Jehoiakim. But he took Jehoahaz away, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10200BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10200BP\"></sup>and he came to Egypt and died there.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>And Jehoiakim <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10201BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10201BQ\"></sup>gave the silver and the gold to Pharaoh, but he taxed the land to give the money according to the command of Pharaoh. He exacted the silver and the gold of the people of the land, from everyone according to his assessment, to give it to Pharaoh Neco.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10202BR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BR&quot;&gt;BR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10202BR\"></sup>Jehoiakim was twenty-five years old when he began to reign, and he reigned eleven years in Jerusalem. His mother's name was Zebidah the daughter of Pedaiah of Rumah.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>And he did what was evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10203BS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BS&quot;&gt;BS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10203BS\"></sup>according to all that his fathers had done."
		},
		"24": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">24 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10204A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10204A\"></sup>In his days, Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon came up, and Jehoiakim became his servant for three years. Then he turned and rebelled against him.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> sent against him bands of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10205B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10205B\"></sup>Chaldeans and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10205C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10205C\"></sup>bands of the Syrians and bands of the Moabites and bands of the Ammonites, and sent them against Judah to destroy it, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10205D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10205D\"></sup>according to the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> that he spoke by his servants the prophets.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Surely this came upon Judah at the command of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, to remove them out of his sight, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10206E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10206E\"></sup>for the sins of Manasseh, according to all that he had done,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>and also <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10207F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10207F\"></sup>for the innocent blood that he had shed. For he filled Jerusalem with innocent blood, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> would not pardon.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10208G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10208G\"></sup>Now the rest of the deeds of Jehoiakim and all that he did, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Judah?",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So Jehoiakim <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10209H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10209H\"></sup>slept with his fathers, and Jehoiachin his son reigned in his place.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10210I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10210I\"></sup>And the king of Egypt did not come again out of his land, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10210J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10210J\"></sup>for the king of Babylon had taken all that belonged to the king of Egypt <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10210K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10210K\"></sup>from the Brook of Egypt to the river Euphrates.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10211L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10211L\"></sup>Jehoiachin was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10211M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10211M\"></sup>eighteen years old when he became king, and he reigned three months in Jerusalem. His mother's name was Nehushta the daughter of Elnathan of Jerusalem.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And he did what was evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10212N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10212N\"></sup>according to all that his father had done.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>At that time the servants of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10213O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10213O\"></sup>Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon came up to Jerusalem, and the city was besieged.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10214P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10214P\"></sup>Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon came to the city while his servants were besieging it,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10215Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10215Q\"></sup>and Jehoiachin the king of Judah gave himself up to the king of Babylon, himself and his mother and his servants and his officials and his palace officials. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10215R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10215R\"></sup>The king of Babylon took him prisoner <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10215S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10215S\"></sup>in the eighth year of his reign",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>and carried off all the treasures of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10216T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10216T\"></sup>and the treasures of the king's house, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10216U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10216U\"></sup>and cut in pieces all the vessels of gold in the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10216V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10216V\"></sup>which Solomon king of Israel had made, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10216W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10216W\"></sup>as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had foretold.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10217X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10217X\"></sup>He carried away all Jerusalem and all the officials and all the mighty men of valor, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10217Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10217Y\"></sup>10,000 captives, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10217Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10217Z\"></sup>and all the craftsmen and the smiths. None remained, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10217AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10217AA\"></sup>except the poorest people of the land.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10218AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10218AB\"></sup>And he carried away Jehoiachin to Babylon. The king's mother, the king's wives, his officials, and the chief men of the land he took into captivity from Jerusalem to Babylon.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And the king of Babylon brought captive to Babylon all the men of valor, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10219AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10219AC\"></sup>7,000, and the craftsmen and the metal workers, 1,000, all of them strong and fit for war.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10220AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10220AD\"></sup>And the king of Babylon <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10220AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10220AE\"></sup>made Mattaniah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10220AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10220AF\"></sup>Jehoiachin's uncle, king in his place, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10220AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10220AG\"></sup>and changed his name to Zedekiah.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10221AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10221AH\"></sup>Zedekiah was twenty-one years old when he became king, and he reigned eleven years in Jerusalem. His mother's name was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10221AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10221AI\"></sup>Hamutal the daughter of Jeremiah of Libnah.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And he did what was evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10222AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10222AJ\"></sup>according to all that Jehoiakim had done.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>For because of the anger of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> it came to the point in Jerusalem and Judah that he cast them out from his presence.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10223AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10223AK\"></sup>And Zedekiah rebelled against the king of Babylon."
		},
		"25": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">25 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10224A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10224A\"></sup>And in the ninth year of his reign, in the tenth month, on the tenth day of the month, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10224B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10224B\"></sup>Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon came with all his army against Jerusalem and laid siege to it. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10224C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10224C\"></sup>And they built siegeworks all around it.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>So the city was besieged till the eleventh year of King Zedekiah.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>On the ninth day of the fourth month <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10226D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10226D\"></sup>the famine was so severe in the city that there was no food for the people of the land.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then a breach was made in the city, and all the men of war fled by night by the way of the gate between the two walls, by <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10227E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10227E\"></sup>the king's garden, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10227F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10227F\"></sup>the Chaldeans were around the city. And they went in the direction of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10227G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10227G\"></sup>Arabah.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>But the army of the Chaldeans pursued the king and overtook him in the plains of Jericho, and all his army was scattered from him.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then they captured the king <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10229H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10229H\"></sup>and brought him up to the king of Babylon at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10229I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10229I\"></sup>Riblah, and they passed sentence on him.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>They slaughtered the sons of Zedekiah before his eyes, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10230J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10230J\"></sup>and put out the eyes of Zedekiah and bound him in chains and took him to Babylon.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10231K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10231K\"></sup>In the fifth month, on <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10231L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10231L\"></sup>the seventh day of the month—that was the nineteenth year of King Nebuchadnezzar, king of Babylon—Nebuzaradan, the captain of the bodyguard, a servant of the king of Babylon, came to Jerusalem.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10232M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10232M\"></sup>And he burned the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10232N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10232N\"></sup>and the king's house and all the houses of Jerusalem; every great house he burned down.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And all the army of the Chaldeans, who were with the captain of the guard, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10233O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10233O\"></sup>broke down the walls around Jerusalem.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10234P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10234P\"></sup>And the rest of the people who were left in the city and the deserters who had deserted to the king of Babylon, together with the rest of the multitude, Nebuzaradan the captain of the guard carried into exile.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>But the captain of the guard left <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10235Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10235Q\"></sup>some of the poorest of the land to be vinedressers and plowmen.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10236R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10236R\"></sup>And the pillars <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10236S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10236S\"></sup>of bronze that were in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10236T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10236T\"></sup>the stands and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10236U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10236U\"></sup>the bronze sea that were in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the Chaldeans broke in pieces and carried the bronze to Babylon.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10237V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10237V\"></sup>And they took away the pots and the shovels and the snuffers and the dishes for incense and all the vessels of bronze used in the temple service,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>the fire pans also and the bowls. What was of gold the captain of the guard took away as gold, and what was of silver, as silver.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>As for the two pillars, the one sea, and the stands that Solomon had made for the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10239W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10239W\"></sup>the bronze of all these vessels was beyond weight.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10240X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10240X\"></sup>The height of the one pillar was eighteen cubits, and on it was a capital of bronze. The height of the capital was three cubits. A latticework and pomegranates, all of bronze, were all around the capital. And the second pillar had the same, with the latticework.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10241Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10241Y\"></sup>And the captain of the guard took <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10241Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10241Z\"></sup>Seraiah the chief priest and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10241AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10241AA\"></sup>Zephaniah the second priest and the three keepers of the threshold;",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>and from the city he took an officer who had been in command of the men of war, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10242AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10242AB\"></sup>five men of the king's council who were found in the city; and the secretary of the commander of the army, who mustered the people of the land; and sixty men of the people of the land, who were found in the city.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And Nebuzaradan the captain of the guard took them and brought them to the king of Babylon at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10243AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10243AC\"></sup>Riblah.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And the king of Babylon struck them down and put them to death at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10244AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10244AD\"></sup>Riblah in the land of Hamath. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10244AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10244AE\"></sup>So Judah was taken into exile out of its land.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And over the people who remained in the land of Judah, whom Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon had left, he appointed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10245AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10245AF\"></sup>Gedaliah the son of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10245AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10245AG\"></sup>Ahikam, son of Shaphan, governor.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10246AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10246AH\"></sup>Now when all the captains and their men heard that the king of Babylon had appointed Gedaliah governor, they came with their men to Gedaliah at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10246AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10246AI\"></sup>Mizpah, namely, Ishmael the son of Nethaniah, and Johanan the son of Kareah, and Seraiah the son of Tanhumeth the Netophathite, and Jaazaniah the son of the Maacathite.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And Gedaliah swore to them and their men, saying, “Do not be afraid because of the Chaldean officials. Live in the land and serve the king of Babylon, and it shall be well with you.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10248AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10248AJ\"></sup>But in the seventh month, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10248AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10248AK\"></sup>Ishmael the son of Nethaniah, son of Elishama, of the royal family, came with ten men and struck down Gedaliah and put him to death along with the Jews and the Chaldeans who were with him at Mizpah.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10249AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10249AL\"></sup>Then all the people, both small and great, and the captains of the forces arose and went to Egypt, for they were afraid of the Chaldeans.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10250AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10250AM\"></sup>And in the thirty-seventh year of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10250AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10250AN\"></sup>the exile of Jehoiachin king of Judah, in the twelfth month, on the twenty-seventh day of the month, Evil-merodach king of Babylon, in the year that he began to reign, graciously <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10250AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10250AO\"></sup>freed Jehoiachin king of Judah from prison.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>And he spoke kindly to him and gave him a seat above the seats of the kings who were with him in Babylon.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>So Jehoiachin put off his prison garments. And every day of his life <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10252AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10252AP\"></sup>he dined regularly at the king's table,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>and for his allowance, a regular allowance was given him by the king, according to his daily needs, as long as he lived."
		}
	}
};
